queryText: select a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle from Employee a natural join Department d where (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' or b.deptName = 'Sales') and         (a.annualSalary >= 7000 and a.annualSalary <= 100000) and         (a.empName like '_a%' or a.empName like '_i%') order by a.empName asc, b.deptName desc

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a join Department b on a.deptID = b.deptID  WHERE ((b.deptLocation = 'Dubai') OR (b.deptName = 'Sales')) AND (a.annualSalary >= 84000 AND a.annualSalary <= 120000) AND ((a.empName LIKE '_A%' )OR (a.empName LIKE '_I%')) ORDER BY a.empName,  b.deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND a.annualSalary >= 84000 AND a.annualSalary <= 120000 AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC;

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Department a, Employee b WHERE b.deptID = a.deptID and (deptLocation = 'Dubai' or deptName = 'Sales') and  (annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 and annualSalary / 12 <= 10000)

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a, Department b WHERE (a.deptID = b.deptID) AND (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (a.annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary / 12 <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE '_i%' OR a.empName LIKE '_a%') ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Department a JOIN Employee b ON a.deptID = b.deptID WHERE (deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR deptName = 'Sales') AND (annualSalary)/12 >= 7000 AND (annualSalary)/12 <=10000 AND (empName LIKE '_a%' OR empName LIKE '_i%') ORDER BY empName, deptName DESC;

select a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle from Employee a join Department d on a.deptID = b.deptID where b.deptLocation = 'Dubai'  or b.deptName = 'Sales'  and ((a.annualSalary / 12) >= 7000 and (a.annualSalary / 12) <= 10000) and (a.empName like '_A%' or a.empName like '_I%') order by a.empName asc, b.deptName desc

SELECT b.empName, b.annualSalary, a.deptName, a.deptLocation, b.jobTitle FROM Department a JOIN Employee b ON a.deptID = b.deptID WHERE (a.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR a.deptName = "Sales") AND ( b.annualSalary <= 100000 AND b.annualSalary >= 70000) AND ( b.empName LIKE "_a%" OR b.empName LIKE "_i%") ORDER BY b.empName ASC, a.deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName as Name, a.annualSalary as Salary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee as e INNER JOIN Department as d ON b.deptID = a.deptID WHERE (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR b.deptName = "Sales") AND (a.annualSalary/12 <= 10000 AND a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000) AND (a.empName LIKE "_A%" OR a.empName LIKE "_I%") ORDER BY b.deptName DESC

SELECT b.empName, b.annualSalary, a.deptName, a.deptLocation, b.jobTitle FROM Department a NATURAL JOIN Employee Emp WHERE (a.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR a.deptName = "Sales") AND          (b.annualSalary >= 12 * 7000 AND b.annualSalary <= 12 * 10000) AND          (b.empName LIKE '_A%' OR b.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY b.empName, a.deptName DESC

SELECT Employee.empName, Employee.annualSalary, Department.deptName, Department.deptLocation, Employee.jobTitle FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department WHERE (Department.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR Department.deptName = 'Sales') AND (Employee.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND Employee.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (SUBSTR(Employee.empName, 2, 1) = 'A'  OR SUBSTR(Employee.empName, 2, 1) = 'I')

SELECT b.empName, b.annualSalary, a.deptName, a.deptLocation, b.jobTitle FROM Department a INNER JOIN Employee b on b.deptID = a.deptID WHERE (a.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR a.deptName = 'Sales') AND (b.annualSalary >= 84000 AND b.annualSalary <= 120000) AND (b.empName LIKE "_A%" OR b.empName LIKE "_I%")

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee e JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (a.annualSalary >= 7000 OR a.annualSalary <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName ASC, b.deptName DESC ;

SELECT b.empName, b.annualSalary, a.deptName, a.deptLocation, b.jobTitle  FROM Department a join Employee E on a.deptID = b.deptID where (a.deptLocation = "Dubai" or a.deptName= "sales") and ((b.annualSalary/12) >= 7000 and (b.annualSalary/12) <= 10000)  -- and (b.empName like '_a%' or '_i%') order by b.empName, a.deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR b.deptName = "Sales") AND (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary/12 <=10000) AND (a.empName LIKE "_a%" OR a.empName LIKE "_i%") ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Department, Employee WHERE deptName = "Sales" AND annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND annualSalary/12 <= 10000 AND (empName LIKE "_A%" OR empName LIKE "_I%") AND jobTitle LIKE "Sales%" ORDER BY empName, deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 AND annualSalary / 12 <= 10000) AND (empName LIKE '_A%' OR empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC;

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee AS E JOIN Department AS b ON b.deptID = a.deptId WHERE     (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR b.deptName = "Sales") AND     (a.annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary / 12 <= 10000) AND     (a.empName LIKE "_A%" OR a.empName LIKE "_I%") ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department WHERE (deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR (deptName = 'Sales' AND annualSalary >= 84000 AND annualSalary <= 120000)) AND (empName LIKE '_I%' OR empName LIKE '_A%')  ORDER BY empName ASC, deptName DESC;

SELECT e.empName, e.annualSalary, d.deptName, d.deptLocation, e.jobTitle FROM (Employee e) NATURAL JOIN (Department d) WHERE (d.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR d.deptName = "Sales") AND (e.annualSalary >= 84000 AND e.annualSalary <= 120000) AND (e.empName LIKE "_A%" OR e.empName LIKE "_I%") ORDER BY e.empName, d.deptName DESC

Select b.empName, b.annualSalary, a.deptName, a.deptLocation, b.jobTitle From Department a Natural Join Employee emp WHERE (a.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR a.deptName = "Sales") AND (b.annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 AND b.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (b.empName LIKE '_a%' OR b.empName LIKE '_i%')

select Employee.empName, Employee.annualSalary, Department.deptName,Department.deptLocation, Employee.jobTitle from Employee natural join Department where (Department.deptLocation = 'Dubai' or deptName = 'Sales') and Employee.annualSalary/12>=7000 and Employee.annualSalary/12<= 10000 and (Employee.empName like '_A%' or Employee.empName like '_I%') order by Employee.empName, Department.deptName desc

select a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle from Employee a join Department b on a.deptID = b.deptID where (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' or b.deptName = 'Sales') and ((a.annualSalary/12)>= 7000 and (a.annualSalary/12) <= 10000) and (a.empName LIKE '_A%' or a.empName LIKE '_I%') order by a.empName, b.deptName desc

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID  WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (a.annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary / 12 <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

SELECT E1.empName, E1.annualSalary, D1.deptName, D1.deptLocation, E1.jobTitle FROM (Employee E1 INNER JOIN Department D1 ON D1.deptID = E1.DeptID) WHERE (D1.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR D1.deptName = 'Sales') AND (E1.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND E1.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (E1.empName LIKE '_A%' OR E1.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY E1.empName, D1.deptName DESC

Select Employee.empName, Employee.annualSalary, Department.deptName, Department.deptLocation, Employee.jobTitle From Department, Employee Where Employee.deptID = Department.deptID AND Employee.annualSalary>= 94000 AND Employee.annualSalary<= 120000 AND ((Employee.empname LIKE '_a%') OR (Employee.empname LIKE '_i%')) AND ((Department.deptlocation = "Dubai") OR (Department.deptName = "Sales")) Order by Employee.empname, Department.deptName DESC

SELECt Employee.empName, Employee.annualSalary, Department.deptName, Department.deptLocation, Employee.jobTitle FROM Employee, Department WHERE (Employee.deptID = Department.deptID) AND (Department.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR Department.deptName = 'Sales') AND (Employee.annualSalary/12 <= 10000.0 && Employee.annualSalary/12 >= 7000.0) AND (Employee.empName LIKE '_a%' OR Employee.empName LIKE '_i%')

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Department, Employee WHERE (deptName = "Sales") AND (annualSalary/12 BETWEEN 7000 AND 10000) AND (empName LIKE '_A%' OR empName LIKE '_I%') AND jobTitle LIKE "Sales%" ORDER BY empName ASC, deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a INNER JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptId WHERE ((b.deptLocation LIKE "Dubai" OR b.deptName LIKE "Sales") AND (a.annualSalary/12 BETWEEN 7000 AND 10000)) AND (a.empName LIKE "_a%" OR a.empName LIKE "_i%") ORDER BY a.empName ASC, b.deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE      (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND      ((a.annualSalary / 12 >= 7000) AND (a.annualSalary / 12 <= 10000)) AND      (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC;

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a, Department b WHERE a.deptId = b.deptId AND (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR b.deptName = "Sales")     AND (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary/12 <=10000)      AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%')

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a, Department b WHERE (b.deptID = a.deptID) AND (b.deptLocation = 'DUBAI' OR b.deptName = 'SALES') AND (a.annualSalary/12 BETWEEN 7000 AND 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE "_A%" OR a.empName LIKE "_I%")

select a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle from Employee a natural join Department d where (b.deptLocation='Dubai' or b.deptName='Sales') and (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 or a.annualSalary <= 10000) and (a.empName like '%a%' or a.empName like '%i%')

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department WHERE (deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR deptName = 'Sales') AND annualSalary >= 7000 AND annualSalary <= 100000 AND empName LIKE '_i%' ORDER BY empName ASC, deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Employee e NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE (deptLocation LIKE "Dubai" OR deptName LIKE "Sales") AND     (annualSalary >= 7000*12 AND annualSalary <= 10000*12) AND     (empName LIKE "_A%" OR empName LIKE "_I%" OR empName LIKE "_a%" OR empName LIKE "_i%") ORDER BY empName, deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee E     JOIN Department b ON b.deptID = a.deptID WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND       ((a.annualSalary / 12) >= 7000 AND (a.annualSalary / 12) <= 10000) AND       (empName LIKE '_A%' OR empName LIKE '_I%' OR empName LIKE '_a%' OR empName LIKE '_i%')

select a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle from Employee a inner join Department b on a.deptId = b.deptId where (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" or b.deptName = "Sales") and  ((a.annualSalary / 12) <= 10000 or (a.annualSalary / 12) >= 7000) and (a.empName like "_A%" or a.empName like "_I%")

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department d WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE "_A%" OR a.empName LIKE "_I%") ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

select empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle from Employee natural join Department where (deptLocation = "Dubai" or deptName = "Sales")     and (annualSalary / 12 >= 7000 and annualSalary / 12 <= 10000)     and (empName like "_A%" or empName like "_I%") order by empName, deptName desc

SELECT Employee.empName, Employee.annualSalary, Department.deptName, Department.deptLocation, Employee.jobTitle  FROM Employee INNER JOIN Department on Employee.deptId = Department.deptId WHERE (Department.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR Department.deptName = 'Sales') AND (Employee.empName LIKE '_I%' OR Employee.empName LIKE '_A%') GROUP BY Employee.empId ORDER BY Employee.empName ASC, Department.deptName DESC;

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee as e JOIN Department as d ON a.deptID = b.deptID WHERE (b.deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR b.deptName = 'Sales') AND (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') ORDER BY a.empName ASC, b.deptName DESC

Select a.empName,a.annualSalary,b.deptName,b.deptLocation,a.jobTitle from Employee a,Department b,Salary_Grade c where a.deptID=b.deptID and a.annualSalary >= c.minAnnualSalary and a.annualSalary <= c.maxAnnualSalary and (b.deptLocation LIKE 'Dubai' OR b.deptName LIKE 'Sales') and  (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 and a.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) and (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') order by a.empName,b.deptName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle  FROM Employee a, Department b WHERE a.deptId = b.deptId      AND (b.deptLocation = "Dubai" OR b.deptName = "Sales")     AND ((a.empName LIKE "_a%") OR (a.empName LIKE "_i%"));

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary, b.deptName, b.deptLocation, a.jobTitle FROM Employee a, Department b WHERE ((b.deptName = "Sales" AND a.jobTitle LIKE '%Sales%')) AND (a.annualSalary/12 >= 7000 AND a.annualSalary/12 <= 10000) AND (a.empName LIKE '_A%' OR a.empName LIKE '_I%') AND a.annualSalary IN (SELECT e2.annualSalary FROM Employee e2, Salary_Grade s WHERE e2.annualSalary >= s.minAnnualSalary AND e2.annualSalary <= s.maxAnnualSalary) ORDER BY a.empName, b.deptName DESC

SELECT empName, annualSalary, deptName, deptLocation, jobTitle FROM Employee emp JOIN Department dept ON b.deptID = a.deptID WHERE (deptLocation = 'Dubai' OR deptName = 'Sales')  AND (annualSalary >= 84000 AND annualSalary	<= 120000)  AND (empName LIKE '_A%' OR empName LIKE '_I%')

SELECT a.empName, a.annualSalary/12 as monthlySalary, b.deptName, a.hireDate FROM Employee a JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID WHERE a.hireDate IN (SELECT MAX(hireDate) FROM Employee where deptID=a.deptID) AND a.annualSalary >=(SELECT minAnnualSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade =12) AND a.annualSalary <=(SELECT maxAnnualSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade =12) ORDER BY a.empName, monthlySalary DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.deptID) as empCnt FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b on a.deptID = b.deptID  GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY empCnt ASC, a.deptName DESC
Select a.deptName, a.deptLocation, Count(b.empID) as empCNT from Department a Left outer join Employee b On (a.deptID = b.deptID) group by  a.deptID order by empCNT, a.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) as empCnt FROM Department a LEFT JOIN Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY empCnt, a.deptName DESC;
SELECT b.deptName, b.deptLocation, COUNT(DISTINCT(a.empID)) FROM Employee a RIGHT OUTER JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY b.deptID ORDER BY COUNT(DISTINCT(a.empID)), b.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) as empCNT FROM Department a  LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY a.deptId ORDER BY empCNT, a.deptName DESC;
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) FROM Department d LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee e ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY a.deptName, a.deptLocation ORDER BY COUNT(b.empID), a.deptName DESC

SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.deptID) FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY a.deptName, a.deptLocation, a.deptID ORDER BY COUNT(b.deptID), a.deptName DESC

SELECT deptName, deptLocation, count(empID) as total_employee FROM Department LEFT JOIN Employee ON Department.deptID = Employee.deptID GROUP BY Department.deptID ORDER BY total_employee ASC, deptName DESC;
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) AS numEmployees FROM Department d LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee e ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY numEmployees ASC, a.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(empID) as empCnt FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY deptName, deptLocation ORDER BY empCnt, deptName DESC
SELECT b.deptName, b.deptLocation, count(a.empID) FROM Employee a RIGHT JOIN Department d         on a.deptID = b.deptID  GROUP BY b.deptID ORDER BY count(a.empID) ASC, b.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a. deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) as empIDCount From Department a LEFT Outer Join Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY empIDCount, a.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) AS empCount FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY a.deptID  ORDER BY empCount ASC, deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) AS cnt FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON a.deptID = b.deptID GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY cnt, a.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, count(b.empID) AS "count" FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY count, a.deptName DESC

Select b.deptName,b.deptLocation,count(a.empID) AS num_employees from Employee a RIGHT JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID  group by b.deptName,b.deptLocation order by num_employees,b.deptName DESC
SELECT a.deptName, a.deptLocation, COUNT(b.empID) AS empCnt FROM Department a LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) GROUP BY a.deptID ORDER BY empCnt, a.deptName DESC;

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary/12, Employee.deptID, deptName, grade FROM Employee JOIN Salary_Grade      ON Employee.salary > Salary_Grade.minSalary AND Employee.salary <= Salary_Grade.maxSalary  JOIN Department ON Department.deptID = Employee.deptID WHERE salary/12 > 7000 OR jobTitle <> "IT Support"

select ee.empName, ee.jobTitle, ee.salary/12, ee.deptID, deptName, grade FROM (Employee ee JOIN Department de ON ee.deptID = de.deptID) JOIN Salary_Grade a ON ee.salary BETWEEN a.minSalary AND a.maxSalary WHERE ee.salary/12 > 7000 OR NOT (ee.jobTitle = "IT Support")

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary / 12, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID = b.deptID AND a.salary >= c.minSalary AND a.salary <= c.maxSalary AND (a.salary/12 > 7000 OR a.empID NOT IN (SELECT empID FROM Employee WHERE jobTitle <> 'IT Support'))

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department b JOIN Salary_Grade c ON (a.salary >= c.minSalary AND a.salary <= c.maxSalary) WHERE a.salary/12 > 7000 OR a.jobTitle <> 'IT Support'

Select a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 as monthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade From Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c Where ((a.salary/12)>7000 OR a.jobTitle <> 'IT Support') AND a.deptID = b.deptID AND (a.salary between c.minsalary and c.maxsalary)

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary/12, deptID, deptName, grade FROM Department NATURAL JOIN Employee JOIN Salary_Grade ON salary >= minSalary AND salary <= maxSalary WHERE salary > 7000 OR jobTitle NOT LIKE 'IT Support'

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary/12, deptID, deptName, grade  FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department, Salary_Grade WHERE (salary > minSalary AND salary <= maxSalary) AND  (salary/12 > 7000 OR jobTitle NOT LIKE "%IT Support%")

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary/12, deptID, deptName, grade FROM Department NATURAL JOIN Employee, Salary_Grade WHERE salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary AND (salary/12 >= 7000 OR jobTitle <> "IT Support")

SELECT DISTINCT a.empName, a.jobTitle, (a.salary/12), a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department b LEFT OUTER JOIN Salary_Grade c ON ((a.salary >= c.minSalary) AND (a.salary <= c.maxSalary)) WHERE (a.salary/12) > 7000 OR a.jobTitle <> 'IT Support'

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12.0 as MonthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.DeptID = b.deptID AND a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary AND (((a.salary/12.0)>7000) OR (a.jobTitle <> "IT Support"));

select empName, jobTitle, (salary / 12) as monthlySalary, deptID, deptName, grade from Employee a natural join Department d join Salary_Grade c on a.salary >= c.minSalary and a.salary <= c.maxSalary where salary / 12 > 7000 or jobTitle != 'IT Support'

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary / 12, deptID, deptName, grade FROM (Employee NATURAL JOIN Department), Salary_Grade WHERE salary >= minSalary AND salary <= maxSalary AND (salary > 7000 OR jobTitle != 'IT Support');

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 AS monthly_salary, b.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE ((a.salary/12 > 7000) OR (b.deptName <> "IT Support")) AND (a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary ) AND (a.deptID = b.deptID)

select a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12, a.deptId, b.deptName, c.grade from Employee a natural join Department b, Salary_Grade c where (a.salary/12>7000 or a.jobTitle<>"IT Support") and (a.salary between c.minSalary and c.maxSalary)

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, (a.salary/12) as MonthlySal, b.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID=b.deptID AND (a.salary>=c.minSalary AND a.salary<=c.maxSalary)  AND (a.salary/12>7000 OR a.jobTitle<>"IT Support")

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12.0 as MonthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.DeptID = b.deptID AND a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary AND (((a.salary/12.0)>7000) OR (a.jobTitle <> "IT Support"));

select empName, jobTitle, salary/12, emp.deptID, deptName, grade from (Employee emp JOIN Department dept on emp.deptID = dept.deptID), Salary_Grade where (salary > (7000/12) and salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary) ;

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary/12, deptID, deptName, grade FROM Department NATURAL JOIN (SELECT * FROM Employee JOIN Salary_Grade ON salary >= minSalary AND salary <= maxSalary) as sal WHERE a.salary/12 > 7000;

SELECT Employee.empName, Employee.jobTitle, Employee.salary/12, Department.deptID, Department.deptName, Salary_Grade.grade FROM Employee INNER JOIN Department ON Employee.deptID = Department.deptID CROSS JOIN Salary_Grade WHERE (Employee.salary >= Salary_Grade.minSalary AND Employee.salary <= Salary_Grade.maxSalary AND (Employee.salary/12 > 7000 OR Employee.jobTitle <> 'IT Support'))

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 as "Monthly Salary", a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID = b.deptID     AND a.salary between c.minSalary and c.maxSalary     AND (a.salary/12 > 7000 or a.jobTitle != "IT Support")

select empName, jobTitle, salary/12, emp.deptID, deptName, grade from (Employee emp JOIN Department dept on emp.deptID = dept.deptID), Salary_Grade where (salary > (7000/12) and salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary) ;

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary / 12, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee e     JOIN Department b ON a.deptID = b.deptID     JOIN Salary_Grade c ON (a.salary >= c.minSalary) AND (a.salary <= c.maxSalary) WHERE (a.salary / 12 > 7000) OR (a.jobTitle <> "IT Support")

SELECT DISTINCT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 as MonthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department b JOIN Salary_Grade c ON (a.salary <= c.maxSalary AND a.salary >= c.minSalary) WHERE a.jobTitle <> "IT Support" OR (a.salary/12) > 7000

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 AS MonthlySal, b.deptId, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE (a.deptId = b.deptId) AND (a.salary >= c.minSalary AND a.salary <= c.maxSalary) AND (a.salary/12 > 7000 OR a.jobTitle != "IT Support")

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12 AS MonthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE (a.jobTitle <> "IT Support" OR (a.salary/12) > 7000) AND a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, (a.salary/12) as monthlySalary, a.deptID, c.deptName, b.grade FROM Employee E LEFT OUTER JOIN Salary_Grade b ON a.salary BETWEEN b.minSalary AND b.maxSalary LEFT OUTER JOIN Department c ON a.deptID = c.deptID WHERE a.salary/12 > 7000     OR a.jobTitle NOT LIKE 'IT Support' ORDER BY b.grade, a.empName DESC

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary / 12, a.deptID, c.deptName, b.grade FROM Employee a       JOIN Salary_Grade b ON a.salary BETWEEN b.minSalary AND b.maxSalary      JOIN Department c ON a.deptID = c.deptID WHERE a.deptID != 'IT Support' AND a.salary > 12 * 7000

select empName, jobTitle, salary / 12 as MonthlySal, deptID, deptName, grade from (Department natural join Employee) join Salary_Grade on salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary where salary / 12 > 7000 or jobTitle <> "IT Support"

Select DISTINCT empName,jobTitle,(salary/12),deptID,deptName,grade from Employee Natural Join Department,Salary_Grade where (salary>=minSalary and salary<=maxSalary ) and (salary > 7000 or jobTitle NOT LIKE "IT Support")

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12.0 as MonthlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.DeptID = b.deptID     AND a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary     AND (((a.salary/12.0)>7000) OR (a.jobTitle <> "IT Support"));

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12, b.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROm Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID = b.deptID AND a.salary >= c.minSalary AND a.salary <= c.maxSalary AND (a.salary/12 > 7000 OR a.jobTitle <> "IT Support")

SELECT empName, jobTitle, salary / 12, deptID, deptName, grade FROM (Employee NATURAL JOIN Department) JOIN Salary_Grade          ON (Employee.salary >= Salary_Grade.minSalary AND Employee.salary <= Salary_Grade.maxSalary) WHERE salary / 12 > 7000 OR jobTitle <> "IT Support";

SELECT a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.salary/12.0 as MontlySal, a.deptID, b.deptName, c.grade FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID = b.deptID     AND a.salary BETWEEN c.minSalary AND c.maxSalary     AND (((a.salary/12.0) > 7000) OR (a.jobTitle <> 'IT Support'));
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE deptID = (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = 'London')

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE Employee.salary > (SELECT minSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE Salary_Grade.grade = 12) AND Employee.salary < (SELECT maxSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE Salary_Grade.grade = 13) AND Employee.deptID = (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = "London")

SELECT a.* FROM Employee a JOIN Salary_Grade b ON (b.grade = 13 OR b.grade = 12) AND       a.salary <= b.maxSalary AND a.salary >= b.minSalary WHERE a.deptID IN (SELECT de.deptID FROM Department de WHERE de.deptLocation = "LONDON")

SELECT * FROM Employee e WHERE a.empID IN (SELECT a.empID FROM Employee e, Department d WHERE a.deptID = d.deptID AND d.deptLocation = 'London' AND a.empID IN (SELECT a.empID FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s WHERE (a.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary) AND s.grade IN (12, 13)))

SELECT a.empID, a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.managerID, a.hireDate, a.salary, a.comission, a.deptID FROM Employee a NATURAL JOIN Department b JOIN Salary_Grade c ON (a.salary > c.minSalary AND a.salary < c.maxSalary) WHERE b.deptLocation = 'London' AND (c.grade = 12 OR c.grade = 13)

Select empID, empName, jobTitle,managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, a.deptID From Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c Where c.grade IN (12,13) AND a.salary Between c.minSalary And c.maxSalary AND a.deptID=b.deptID AND b.deptLocation = 'London'

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE deptID = (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = 'London') AND salary >= (SELECT minSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade = 12) AND salary <= (SELECT maxSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade = 13)

SELECT empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, deptID FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department, Salary_Grade WHERE (Employee.salary > Salary_Grade.minSalary AND Employee.salary < Salary_Grade.maxSalary) AND (Salary_Grade.grade = 12 OR Salary_Grade.grade = 13) AND Department.deptLocation = "London"

SELECT empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, deptID FROM Employee NATURAL JOIN Department, Salary_Grade WHERE grade in (12, 13)  AND salary >= minSalary AND salary <= maxSalary AND deptLocation = "London"
SELECT DISTINCT e.* FROM (Employee e NATURAL JOIN Department d) LEFT OUTER JOIN Salary_Grade a ON (a.grade = 12 OR a.grade = 13) WHERE d.deptLocation = 'London'

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s WHERE (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary) AND s.grade IN (12,13)) AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID FROM Department d WHERE d.deptLocation = "London");

select empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, deptID from Employee a natural join Department d join Salary_Grade c on a.salary >= c.minSalary and a.salary <= c.maxSalary where (grade = 12 or grade = 13) and deptLocation = 'London'

SELECT a.* FROM Employee E WHERE (a.salary <= (SELECT maxSalary from Salary_Grade where grade = 13) AND a.salary >= (SELECT minSalary from Salary_Grade where grade = 12)) AND (a.deptID in (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = 'London'));

select * from Employee where empID in (select empID from Department natural join Employee, Salary_Grade s where (Employee.salary between s.minSalary and s.maxSalary) and (s.grade in (12,13)) and (Department.deptLocation="London"))
SELECT a.* FROM Employee a, Department b, Salary_Grade c WHERE a.deptID=b.deptID AND c.grade IN (12,13) and b.deptLocation = "London" AND salary<=maxSalary AND salary>=minSalary

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID     FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s     WHERE (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary)     AND s.grade IN (12,13)) AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID     FROM Department d     WHERE d.deptLocation = "London");
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE     deptID = (SELECT deptID               FROM Department               WHERE deptLocation = "London")

SELECT Employee.* FROM (SELECT *        FROM Employee       WHERE Employee.deptID in (SELECT Department.deptID FROM Department WHERE Department.deptLocation = 'London')) as Employee, Salary_Grade WHERE      (Employee.salary >= Salary_Grade.minSalary and Employee.salary <= Salary_Grade.maxSalary and (Salary_Grade.grade = 12 or Salary_Grade.grade = 13))

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE deptID IN (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = 'London') AND salary >= (SELECT minSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade = 12) AND salary <= (SELECT maxSalary FROM Salary_Grade where grade = 13);

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE Employee.Salary >        (SELECT Salary_Grade.minSalary        FROM Salary_Grade        WHERE Salary_Grade.grade = 12) AND        Employee.Salary <        (SELECT Salary_Grade.maxSalary        FROM Salary_Grade        WHERE Salary_Grade.grade = 13) AND        'London' =        (SELECT Department.deptLocation         FROM Department         WHERE Department.deptID = Employee.deptID)

SELECT * FROM Employee       WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s WHERE (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary) AND s.grade IN (12,13)) AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID FROM Department d WHERE d.deptLocation = "London");

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT ee.empID FROM Employee ee Join Salary_Grade sg ON (sg.grade = 12 OR sg.grade = 13) AND ee.salary Between sg.minSalary and sg.maxSalary) and deptID in (SElECT deptID from Department Where deptLocation = "London")

select empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate,salary, comission, emp.deptID from (Employee emp JOIN Department dept on emp.deptID = dept.deptID), Salary_Grade where deptLocation = 'London' and (grade = 12 or grade = 13) and (salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary);

SELECT a.empID, a.empName, a.jobTitle, a.managerID, a.hireDate, a.salary, a.comission, a.deptID FROM Employee a JOIN Department b ON (a.deptID = b.deptID) WHERE     b.deptLocation = "London"      AND a.salary >= (     SELECT minSalary     FROM Salary_Grade     WHERE grade = 12 )      AND a.salary <= (     SELECT maxSalary     FROM Salary_Grade     WHERE grade = 13 )

SELECT DISTINCT e.empID, e.empName, e.jobTitle, e.managerID, e.hireDate, e.salary, e.comission, e.deptID FROM Salary_Grade s, Department d, Employee e WHERE s.grade IN (12,13) AND (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary) AND e.deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID FROM Department d WHERE d.deptLocation="London")

SELECT a.* FROM Employee a, Salary_Grade b, Department c WHERE ((b.grade = 12 AND a.salary > b.minSalary AND a.salary < b.maxSalary) OR (b.grade = 13 AND a.salary > b.minSalary AND a.salary < b.maxSalary)) AND a.deptID = c.deptID AND deptLocation = "London"

SELECT * FROM Employee em WHERE a.empID IN (SELECT e.empID FROM Employee e NATURAL JOIN Department d, Salary_Grade sg WHERE d.deptLocation = "London" AND sg.grade in (12, 13) AND e.salary BETWEEN sg.minSalary AND sg.maxSalary)
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empName = ANY(SELECT empName FROM Department LEFT OUTER JOIN Employee on Department.deptID = Employee.deptID WHERE deptLocation = "London")

select DISTINCT empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, Employee.deptID from Employee, Salary_Grade, Department where (grade = 13 or grade = 12) AND Employee.deptID = Department.deptID AND deptLocation = 'London';

SELECT a.* FROM Employee E LEFT OUTER JOIN Salary_Grade b ON a.salary BETWEEN b.minSalary AND b.maxSalary LEFT OUTER JOIN Department c ON a.deptID = c.deptID WHERE b.grade IN (12, 13)     AND c.deptLocation LIKE 'LONDON' ORDER BY a.empId

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE salary BETWEEN (SELECT minSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade = 12)              AND              (SELECT maxSalary FROM Salary_Grade WHERE grade = 13)       AND deptID IN (SELECT deptID FROM Department WHERE deptLocation = 'London')

select empID, empName, jobTitle, managerID, hireDate, salary, comission, deptID from (Department natural join Employee) join Salary_Grade on salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary where (grade = 12 or grade = 13) and deptLocation = "London"

Select * from Employee where empName IN ( Select empName from Employee,Department,Salary_Grade where Employee.deptID = Department.deptID and (salary >= minSalary and salary <= maxSalary) and grade IN (12,13) and deptLocation LIKE 'London' )

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID                 FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s                 WHERE (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary)                         AND s.grade IN (12,13))                         AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID                                        FROM Department d                                        WHERE d.deptLocation = "London");

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s WHERE (e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary) AND s.grade IN (12,13)) AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID FROM Department d WHERE d.deptLocation = "London");

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE deptID IN (     SELECT deptID     FROM Department     WHERE deptLocation = "London" ) AND salary >= (     SELECT minSalary     FROM Salary_Grade     WHERE grade = 12 ) AND salary <= (     SELECT maxSalary     FROM Salary_Grade     WHERE grade = 13 );

SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE empID IN (SELECT e.empID                 FROM Employee e, Salary_Grade s                 WHERE(e.salary BETWEEN s.minSalary AND s.maxSalary)                 AND s.grade IN (12, 13))                 AND deptID IN (SELECT d.deptID                                FROM Department d                                WHERE d.deptLocation = 'London');
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, Firstname ASC;

select distinct a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.sc from Students a, (select e.NetId, sum(e.Credits) as sc  from Students s natural join Enrollments e        group by e.NetId) as b where a.NetId = b.NetId and b.sc > 12 ORDER BY b.sc DESC , a.FirstName ASC;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students s NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students Natural Join Enrollments Group by NetId Having SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER by SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) as total_credits FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY NetId HAVING total_credits > 12 ORDER BY total_credits DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, totalc FROM Students a, (Select b, Sum(Credits) as totalc     From Enrollments E     Group BY NetId     Having Sum(Credits) > 12) Eg Where a.NetId = Eg.NetId   ORDER BY totalc Desc, a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, (SELECT SUM(Credits) FROM Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId) AS CreditHours From Students WHERE (SELECT SUM(Credits) FROM Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId) > 12 ORDER BY CreditHours DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students JOIN Enrollments ON Enrollments.NetId = Students.NetId GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits)>12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Credits)  from Students as a natural join Enrollments as b  group by NetId having sum(Credits) > 12 order by sum(Credits) desc, FirstName asc
Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) as tot From Students a Join Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId Group by b.NetId Having tot >= 13 Order by tot Desc, a.FirstName Asc;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Enrollments NATURAL JOIN Students GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) as TotalCredits from Students a, Enrollments b where a.NetId = b.NetId group by a.NetId having TotalCredits > 12 order by TotalCredits desc, a.FirstName;

Select FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, tot FROM Students a JOIN                      (Select NetId, SUM(Credits) as tot                     FROM Enrollments                     GROUP by NetId                     HAVING tot > 12) d                 ON a.NetId = b.NetId ORDER BY tot DESC, FirstName ASC
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as tot FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY NetId HAVING tot > 12 ORDER BY tot DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.CreditSum FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN (       SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS CreditSum       FROM Enrollments        GROUP BY NetId     ) E WHERE b.CreditSum > 12 ORDER BY b.CreditSum DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

Select *  From (Select Distinct FirstName, LastName, Enrollments.NetId, sum(credits) as creds From Students, Enrollments Where Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId Group By Enrollments.NetId, FirstName, LastName ) as a Where a.creds > 12 Order By  a.creds DESC, FirstName ASC;
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a Natural Join Enrollments e GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 Order By SUM(b.Credits) Desc, a.NetId

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, a.total FROM (SELECT NetId, FirstName, LastName, SUM(Credits) AS total FROM Enrollments NATURAL JOIN Students GROUP BY NetId) as temp WHERE a.total > 12 ORDER BY a.total DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.TotalCredits FROM Students s	JOIN      (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredits     FROM Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId) b ON a.NetId = b.NetId WHERE b.TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY b.TotalCredits DESC, a.FirstName

SElECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SumCredit   FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (         SELECT SUM(Credits) AS SumCredit, NetId           FROM Enrollments          GROUP BY NetId)  a    WHERE SumCredit > 12 ORDER BY SumCredit DESC, FirstName
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) as Nima FROM Students, Enrollments, (SELECT b.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as shabi From Enrollments as b Group BY b.NetId)as Cao WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId AND Students.NetId = Cao.NetId AND Cao.shabi > 12 GROUP BY NetId ORDER BY  Nima DESC , Students.FirstName;

SELECT S.FirstName, S.LastName, S.NetId, StoTC.TC FROM (SELECT S.NetId, SUM(E.Credits) as TC FROM Students S, Enrollments E WHERE S.NetId=E.NetId GROUP BY S.NetID) AS StoTC, Students S WHERE StoTC.TC>12 and S.NetId=StoTC.NetId ORDER BY StoTC.TC DESC, S.FirstName

SELECT      Students.FirstName,     Students.LastName,     Students.NetId,     sum(Enrollments.Credits) FROM      Students, Enrollments WHERE      Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId  Having sum(Enrollments.Credits) > 12  ORDER BY          sum(Enrollments.Credits) DESC,     Students.FirstName ASC;
select FirstName, LastName, NetID, sum(Credits) from Students Natural Join Enrollments group by NetId having sum(Credits) > 12 order by sum(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as numCredits  FROM Students a join Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId group by b.NetId having numCredits > 12 order by numCredits desc, a.FirstName
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a JOIN Enrollments E ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName
select a.FirstName,a.LastName, a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) as total from Students S join Enrollments b on a.NetId=b.NetId group by b.NetId having total>12 order by total desc, a.FirstName asc;

Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, sub.total From  Students a, ( Select e.netid, sum(e.credits) AS total From Enrollments e Group by e.netid ) sub Where a.netid = sub.netid && sub.total > 12 Order by sub.total DESC, a.firstname

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC

SELECT  FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, SUM(Credits) AS total_credits FROM    Students a LEFT JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING  total_credits > 12 ORDER BY total_credits DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, TotalCredits FROM Students, (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS StudentWorkLoads WHERE Students.NetId = StudentWorkLoads.NetId AND StudentWorkLoads.TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, FirstName ASC;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students INNER JOIN Enrollments ON (Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId) GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT b.FirstName , b.LastName, b.NetId, a.sum_credit FROM (SELECT SUM(Credits) sum_credit, NetId FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) a JOIN Students b ON a.NetId = b.NetId WHERE a.sum_credit > 12 ORDER BY a.sum_credit DESC, b.FirstName ASC
select a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, sum(b.Credits) as creds from Students a join Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId group by b.NetId having creds > 12 order by creds desc, a.FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, b.NetId, SUM(a.Credits) FROM Enrollments a JOIN Students b ON b.NetId = a.NetId JOIN Courses c ON c.CRN = a.CRN GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(a.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(a.Credits) DESC, FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, total_credits FROM (SELECT FirstName, LastName, s.NetId, SUM(Credits) as total_credits FROM Students s NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY s.NetId) AS sub WHERE total_credits > 12 ORDER BY total_credits DESC, FirstName
SELECT b.FirstName, b.LastName, a.NetId, sum(a.Credits) sum_creds FROM Enrollments a NATURAL JOIN Students s GROUP by a.NetId HAVING sum(a.Credits) > 12 ORDER by sum_creds DESC, b.firstName ASC

SELECT b.FirstName, b.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(a.Credits) FROM Enrollments a LEFT JOIN Students S ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(a.Credits)>12  ORDER BY SUM(a.Credits) DESC, b.FirstName ;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

Select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) from Students, Enrollments where Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId group by Students.NetId having sum(Credits) > 12  order by sum(Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, temp.sumCredits From Students a,    (SELECT b, SUM(Credits) sumCredits                     FROM Enrollments                     GROUP BY b                     HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12) AS temp WHERE a.NetId = temp.NetId ORDER BY temp.SumCredits DESC, a.FirstName
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments  GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits)>12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) as Credits FROM Students INNER JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetID GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING Credits > 12 ORDER BY Credits DESC, Students.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY FirstName, LastName, NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students s   JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, temp.CRD FROM Students a, (SELECT S.NetId, SUM(Credits) AS CRD     FROM Students S NATURAL JOIN Enrollments E     GROUP BY S.NetId) AS temp      WHERE temp.CRD > 12 AND a.NetId = temp.NetId ORDER BY temp.CRD DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName,LastName,Students.NetId,SUM(credits) FROM Enrollments LEFT OUTER JOIN Students  ON Enrollments.NetId = Students.NetId GROUP BY NetId  HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(credits) DESC ,FirstName ASC;
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Enrollments.Credits) as total from Students natural join Enrollments group by Students.NetId having total >12 order by total DESC, Students.FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits)  FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments  GROUP BY Students.NetId  HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12  ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

select b.FirstName, b.LastName, b.NetId, b.sum_credits from Students b join (select NetId,sum(credits) as sum_credits from Enrollments group by NetId having sum(credits) > 12 ) as b on b.NetId = b.NetId order by b.sum_credits desc, b.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students, Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, sum(Enrollments.Credits) as CreditsSum from Students join Enrollments on Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId group by NetId having sum(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 order by CreditsSum desc, FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as credits FROM Students a INNER JOIN Enrollments e ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING credits > 12 ORDER BY credits DESC, a.FirstName;

select      FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, b.totalCredits from     Students s     inner join         (select              NetId, sum(Credits) totalCredits         from              Enrollments         group by NetId         having totalCredits > 12) total     on b.NetId = a.NetId order by      b.totalCredits desc, a.FirstName asc

select * from (select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, sum(Enrollments.credits) as total from Students, Enrollments where Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId  GROUP BY Students.NetId Order by total DESC,  Students.FirstName) as T where a.total > 12
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredit FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING TotalCredit > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredit DESC, FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as total_credits FROM 	Students s 	join Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId 	GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING total_credits > 12  	ORDER BY total_credits DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students, Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Enrollments.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC;
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) as total FROM Students a JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId=b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING total > 12 ORDER BY total DESC, a.FirstName ASC

select  a.FirstName, a.LastName,  a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) from Students a inner join Enrollments b on a.NetId=b.NetId group by a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId having sum(b.Credits)>12 order by sum(b.Credits) desc, a.FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Enrollments.NetId, sum(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students,Enrollments  WHERE Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Enrollments.NetId HAVING sum(Enrollments.Credits)>=13 ORDER BY sum(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a LEFT OUTER JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstNAme

select a.FirstName, a.Lastname, a.NetId, sum(b.Credits) from Students s inner join Enrollments e on a.NetId = b.NetId group by a.NetId having sum(b.Credits) > 12 order by sum(b.Credits) desc, a.FirstName asc;

SELECT S.FirstName, S.LastName, S.NetId, T.SumCredits FROM Students AS S,  (SELECT b, SUM(Credits) AS SumCredits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS T WHERE S.NetId = T.NetId AND T.SumCredits > 12 ORDER BY T.SumCredits DESC, S.FirstName;

select FirstName, LastName, NetId, total from ( select FirstName as FirstName, LastName as LastName, S.NetId as NetId, sum(Credits) as total from Students as S left join Enrollments as E on S.NetId = E.NetId  group by S.NetId order by total desc, FirstName asc ) as NM where total > 12

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.Creds FROM Students stud NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) as Creds FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) enr WHERE b.Creds > 12 ORDER BY b.Creds DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

select * from (select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, sum(Enrollments.Credits) as tot from Students left join Enrollments on Enrollments.NetId = Students.NetId group by Students.NetId order by tot desc, Students.FirstName asc) a where a.tot > 12

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, Sum(Enrollments.Credits) AS my_sum FROM Students JOIN Enrollments on Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId  GROUP BY NetId HAVING Sum(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY my_sum DESC, FirstName ASC;
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) from Students natural join Enrollments group by NetId Having SUM(Credits) > 12 order by SUM(Credits) desc, FirstName asc

SELECT Students.FirstName,     Students.LastName,     Students.NetId,     (SELECT SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Enrollments WHERE Enrollments.NetId = Students.NetId) AS totCredits      FROM Students     HAVING totCredits > 12     ORDER BY totCredits DESC, Students.FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, a.NetId, a.cred FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) as cred FROM Enrollments  GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12) as sub ORDER BY a.cred DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.Total FROM Students S JOIN (     SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS Total     FROM Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId     HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ) AS b ON a.NetId = b.NetId ORDER BY b.Total DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, total_credit FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS total_credit FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS Credits WHERE total_credit > 12 ORDER BY total_credit DESC, FirstName ASC;
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) AS credits FROM Students s NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY credits DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students S INNER JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, FirstName
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, NetId, b.x FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN     (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS x FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetID HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12) e ORDER BY x DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) AS TotalCredit  FROM Students JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId  GROUP BY Enrollments.NetId HAVING TotalCredit > 12  ORDER BY TotalCredit DESC, Students.FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SumCredits FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) SumCredits                                     FROM Enrollments                                     GROUP BY NetId) as temp WHERE b.SumCredits > 12 ORDER BY SumCredits DESC, FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students as a INNER JOIN Enrollments as b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) >= 13 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC

Select FirstName, LastName, NetId, b.tcredits From Students a Natural Join (SELECT NetID, SUM(Credits) as tcredits                                 FROM Enrollments                                 Group By NetId) as temp Where b.tcredits > 12 ORDER BY b.tcredits DESC, FirstName ASC;

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, b.Credit from Students as a inner join (select NetId, sum(Credits) as Credit from Enrollments group by NetId) as b on a.NetId = b.NetId where b.Credit > 12 order by b.Credit DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, a.NetId, a.Credits FROM Students NATURAL JOIN  ( SELECT NetId, sum(Credits) AS Credits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING sum(Credits) > 12  )AS a  ORDER BY Credits DESC, FirstName   #ON Students.NetID = a.NetID

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, temp.hours FROM Students,       (SELECT sum(Credits) as hours, NetID       FROM Enrollments       GROUP BY NetID) as temp WHERE temp.hours > 12 AND Students.NetId = temp.NetID ORDER BY temp.hours desc, FirstName ASC;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) as TotalHours FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING TotalHours > 12 ORDER BY TotalHours desc, FirstName asc;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, StudentCredit.TotalCredit FROM Students, (SELECT SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredit, NetId FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) as StudentCredit WHERE Students.NetId = StudentCredit.NetId AND StudentCredit.TotalCredit > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredit DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, sum_credit FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (     SELECT sum(Credits) AS sum_credit, NetId     FROM Enrollments E     group by NetId )S where sum_credit > 12 ORDER BY sum_credit DESC, FirstName ASC;
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Credits) from Students natural join Enrollments group by NetId having sum(Credits)>12 order by sum(Credits) desc, FirstName

SELECT DISTINCT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetID, a.Cre FROM Students LEFT JOIN (     SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS Cre     FROM Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId     HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ) Hours ON Students.NetId = a.NetId WHERE a.Cre > 12 ORDER BY a.Cre DESC, Students.FirstName ASC
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments B GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, temp.NetId, total FROM ((SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS total  FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId)AS temp JOIN Students AS s ON temp.NetId = s.NetId) WHERE total > 12  ORDER BY total DESC, FirstName ASC

select FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId as ID, SumCredits from (select NetId, sum(Credits) as SumCredits from Enrollments group by NetId) as temp, Students where temp.SumCredits>12 and temp.NetId=Students.NetId order by SumCredits desc, FirstName
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetID, sum(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN  Enrollments GROUP BY NetID HAVING sum(Credits)>12 ORDER BY sum(Credits) DESC, FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, SUM(b.Credits) as TotalCredits  FROM Students a JOIN Enrollments b      ON a.NetID = b.NetID GROUP BY b.NetID HAVING TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC,         a.FirstName ASC ;
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) from Students a Natural Join Enrollments E group by NetId having SUM(Credits) > 12 order by SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, Sum(Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b, Courses c WHERE a.NetId=b.NetId AND b.CRN=c.CRN GROUP BY b.NetID HAVING Sum(Credits)>12 ORDER BY Sum(Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students, Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId  GROUP BY Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC

SELECT *  FROM (     SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, Sum(Credits) AS TotalCredits     FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId     ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, FirstName)     AS Temp WHERE a.TotalCredits > 12
SELECT DISTINCT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) AS Total_Credits FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY Total_Credits DESC, FirstName;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) as TotalCredits FROM Students  INNER JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, Students.FirstName;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, sum(Credits) as TotalCredits  FROM Students a LEFT JOIN Enrollments e2     ON a.NetId = e2.NetId     GROUP BY a.NetId Having TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits desc, a.FirstName;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

SELECT DISTINCT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, ( SELECT SUM(Credits)         FROM Enrollments En2         WHERE En2.NetId = a.NetId         GROUP BY En2.NetId       ) AS Total_credits FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE ( SELECT SUM(Credits)         FROM Enrollments En2         WHERE En2.NetId = a.NetId         GROUP BY En2.NetId       ) > 12 ORDER BY Total_credits DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Enrollments.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students RIGHT JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, a.Credits     FROM (     SELECT temp.NetID, temp.Credits      FROM (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) as Credits         FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments         GROUP BY NetId) as temp     WHERE temp.Credits > 12 ) as a NATURAL JOIN Students ORDER BY a.Credits DESC, FirstName ASC
SELECT firstName, lastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetID HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, firstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, a.sm FROM (SELECT SUM(E.Credits) as sm, S.NetId, S.FirstName, S.LastName FROM Students S  NATURAL JOIN Enrollments E GROUP BY E.NetId) as t WHERE a.sm > 12 ORDER BY a.sm desc, a.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(Credits) as hours FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments b  GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY hours DESC, a.FirstName    #Group Enrollments by netID #Aggregate the credit hours for each group (netID) #Return students who take more than 12 credit hours   #GROUP BY NetId #HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12

SELECT s.FirstName, s.LastName, s.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) AS "Total Credit" FROM Students AS s, Enrollments b WHERE b.NetId = s.NetId GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, s.FirstName ASC;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Enrollments.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Enrollments INNER JOIN Students WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Enrollments.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.Firstname, a.LastName, a.NetId, c.tCredits FROM Students a,      (SELECT b, sum(Credits) as tCredits      FROM Enrollments      GROUP BY NetID) c WHERE c.NetID = a.NetId and c.tCredits > 12 ORDER BY tCredits DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) as sumcredits From Students a JOIN Enrollments b on (a.NetId = b.NetId) GROUP BY b.NetId  HAVING sumcredits > 12 ORDER BY sumcredits DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students, Enrollments WHERE Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT * FROM      ( SELECT S.FirstName, S.LastName, S.NetID, SUM(E.Credits) as Credits       FROM Students S, Enrollments E        WHERE S.NetID = E.NetID        GROUP BY NetID) AS temp WHERE a.Credits >  12 ORDER BY Credits DESC, FirstName;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students  JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId Group BY b.NetId  Having SUM(b.Credits)>12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName    -- WHERE ( --         SELECT SUM(b.Credits) --         Group BY b.NetId --         Having COUNT(b.Credits)>3 --         )     #    ORDER BY DESC) #ORDER BY a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum_credit from Students natural join (     select sum(Credits) as sum_credit, NetId     FROM Enrollments E     group by NetId) as A where sum_credit > 12 Order by sum_credit DESC, FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, a.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY FirstName, LastName, a.NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Credits) as totalCredits  from Students natural join Enrollments group by NetId having sum(Credits) > 12 order by totalCredits DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, c.C FROM Students a, (SELECT b, SUM(Credits) as C                   FROM Enrollments                   GROUP BY NetId) as c WHERE a.NetId = c.NetId and c.C > 12 ORDER BY c.C DESC, a.Firstname

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, temp.totCredits FROM Students a, (SELECT e.NetId AS net, SUM(e.Credits) AS totCredits FROM Enrollments e GROUP BY e.NetId HAVING SUM(e.Credits) > 12) AS temp WHERE a.NetId = temp.net ORDER BY temp.totCredits DESC, a.FirstName ASC;
Select FirstName, LastName, Netid, SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits)>12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.sm from Students a join ( select NetId, sum(Credits) as sm from Enrollments e group by e.NetID) b on a.NetId=b.NetId where b.sm > 12 order by b.sm desc, a.FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, (     SELECT SUM(Credits) from Enrollments WHERE NetId=Students.Netid  ) FROM Students WHERE (     SELECT SUM(Credits) from Enrollments WHERE NetId=Students.Netid  ) > 12 order by (     SELECT SUM(Credits) from Enrollments WHERE NetId=Students.Netid  ) DESC, FirstName;

select Students.FirstName,  	   Students.LastName,        Students.NetId,        a.Credits from Students  inner join (   select Enrollments.NetId, sum(Enrollments.Credits) as Credits   from Enrollments   group by Enrollments.NetId ) as a on a.NetId = Students.NetId where a.Credits > 12 order by a.Credits desc, Students.FirstName asc;
Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.credits) from Students a  JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId=b.NetId GROUP by NetId HAVING SUM(b.credits)>12 ORDER BY SUM(b.credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName

select FirstName, LastName,Students.NetId,sum(Enrollments.Credits) as SC from Students  right join Enrollments on Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId group by Students.NetId having SC>12 order by SC DESC,Firstname ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, Sum(b.Credits) as totalCredits FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY totalCredits DESC, a.FirstName ASC
SELECT  FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits)  FROM    Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY LastName, FirstName, NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC;
select firstName, lastName, NetId, sum(Credits) as totalCredits from Enrollments natural join Students group by NetId having totalCredits > 12 order by totalCredits desc, firstName;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments GROUP BY FirstName, LastName, NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC, FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, SUM(b.Credits) as totalcreds FROM Students a NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e GROUP BY a.NetId, a.FirstName, a.LastName HAVING totalcreds > 12 ORDER BY totalcreds DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT DISTINCT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, T.creds FROM Students a, (SELECT SUM(Credits) as b, NetId FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS T WHERE T.creds > 12 AND a.NetId = T.NetId ORDER BY T.creds DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT S.FirstName, S.LastName, S.NetId, enrollInfo.totalCredits FROM Students AS S, (SELECT b, SUM(Credits) As totalCredits     FROM Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId) AS enrollInfo WHERE S.NetId = enrollInfo.NetId     AND enrollInfo.totalCredits > 12 ORDER BY enrollInfo.totalCredits DESC, S.FirstName;

Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a INNER JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, a.total FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(credits) as total                 FROM Enrollments                 GROUP BY NetId                 HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12) AS TotalCredits  ORDER BY a.total DESC, FirstName

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.NetId, sum(b.Credits)  from Students a, Enrollments b where b.NetID = a.NetID group by b.NetId, a.FirstName, a.LastName HAVING  sum(b.Credits) > 12 order by sum(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;

SELECT * FROM      (SELECT s.FirstName as fn, s.LastName, s.NetId, SUM(e.Credits) as creditSum     FROM Students s, Enrollments e     WHERE s.NetId = e.NetId     GROUP BY s.NetId) as t WHERE a.creditSum > 12 ORDER BY a.creditSum DESC, a.fn

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Credits) FROM Students  JOIN Enrollments  ON Students.NetId=Enrollments.NetId  GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING (SUM(Credits) > 12)  ORDER BY SUM(Credits) desc, FirstName asc;

SELECT * FROM (SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(credits) as credits FROM (SELECT * FROM Students S NATURAL JOIN Enrollments E) as temp GROUP BY NetID) as a WHERE (credits > 12) ORDER BY credits DESC, FirstName

select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, a.SC as TotalCredits from Students     inner join (select NetId, sum(Credits) as SC from a group by NetId) a on Students.NetId = a.NetId     where a.SC > 12     order by a.SC desc, Students.FirstName
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Credits) as total from Students natural join Enrollments group by NetId having total > 12 order by total desc, FirstName

SELECT DISTINCT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, totalCredits FROM Students LEFT JOIN (SELECT Enrollments.NetId, SUM(credits) as totalCredits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) as a ON Students.NetId = a.NetId WHERE totalCredits > 12 ORDER BY totalCredits DESC, FirstName

SELECT b.FirstName, b.LastName, b.NetId, b.Sum FROM Students b INNER JOIN     (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) as Sum     FROM Enrollments     GROUP by NetId) AS a WHERE b.NetId = b.NetId AND b.Sum > 12 ORDER BY b.Sum DESC, b.FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, Q.T FROM (SELECT * FROM (SELECT NetId ID, SUM(Credits) T FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) as Temp WHERE Temp.T > 12 ) as Q, Students S WHERE S.NetId = Q.ID ORDER BY Q.T DESC, FirstName ASC
select FirstName, LastName, NetId, sum(Credits) as totalHours from Students natural join Enrollments group by NetId having sum(Credits) > 12 order by totalHours DESC, FirstName ASC;
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) as sum FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments  GROUP BY NetID HAVING sum > 12 ORDER BY sum DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT * FROM (SELECT FirstName, LastName, S.NetID AS NetID, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredits FROM Students S LEFT OUTER JOIN Enrollments E ON S.NetID = E.NetID GROUP BY NetID) as temp WHERE a.TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY a.TotalCredits DESC, a.FirstName
SELECT FirstName,LastName,NetId,SUM(Credits) FROM Students NATURAL JOIN Enrollments  GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Credits) DESC,FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) AS CreditHours FROM Students S LEFT OUTER JOIN Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING CreditHours > 12 ORDER BY CreditHours DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY b.NetID HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, FirstName

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) from Students a inner join Enrollments b on a.NetId = b.NetId group by a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId having SUM(b.Credits) > 12 order by SUM(b.Credits) desc, a.FirstName asc

SELECT S.FirstName, S.LastName, Temp.NetId, Temp.TotalCredits FROM (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredits  FROM Students S NATURAL JOIN Enrollments E WHERE S.NetId = E.NetId GROUP BY NetId) AS Temp, Students S WHERE S.NetId = Temp.NetId AND Temp.TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, FirstName

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetID, TotalCredits FROM (SELECT s.FirstName, s.LastName, s.NetID, SUM(e.Credits) AS TotalCredits       FROM Students s NATURAL JOIN Enrollments e       GROUP BY s.NetID) AS T Where TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, FirstName ASC

select * from (     select FirstName, LastName, Enrollments.NetId, sum(Credits) TotalCredits     from Enrollments     inner join Students     on Enrollments.NetId = Students.NetId     group by Enrollments.NetId ) as t1 where TotalCredits > 12 order by TotalCredits desc, FirstName

select Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetID, sum(Enrollments.Credits) -- from Students join Enrollments on Enrollments.NetID = Students.NetID from Students, Enrollments where Students.NetID = Enrollments.NetID  Group by Students.FirstName,Students.LastName, Students.NetID Having sum(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 order by sum(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName
SELECT a.FirstName,a.LastName,b.NetId,SUM(Credits) as total FROM Students a,Enrollments b WHERE b.NetId = a.NetId GROUP BY a.NetId HAVING total>12 ORDER BY total DESC, FirstName asc

SELECT * FROM (      SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) as TotCredits      FROM Enrollments NATURAL JOIN Students     GROUP BY NetId ) AS CreditTable WHERE a.TotCredits > 12 ORDER BY a.TotCredits DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, creds FROM( SELECT bt.NetId, bt.LastName, bt.FirstName,  SUM(bt.Credits) AS creds FROM( SELECT s.FirstName, s.LastName, s.NetId, e.Credits  FROM Students s JOIN Enrollments e ON s.NetId = e.NetId ) AS bt GROUP BY bt.NetId ) AS st WHERE creds > 12 ORDER BY creds DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

SELECT Students.FirstName, Students.LastName, Students.NetId, SUM(Enrollments.Credits) FROM Students INNER JOIN Enrollments ON Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId GROUP BY Students.NetId HAVING SUM(Enrollments.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(Enrollments.Credits) DESC, Students.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, b.TotalCredits FROM Students AS s JOIN (SELECT Enrollmenta.NetId, SUM(Enrollmenta.Credits) AS TotalCredits       FROM Enrollments       GROUP BY Enrollmenta.NetId) AS e ON a.NetId = b.NetId WHERE b.TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY b.TotalCredits desc, a.FirstName asc
select b.FirstName, b.LastName, b.NetId, sum(a.Credits) as temp from Enrollments a join Students b on a.netid = b.netid group by netid having temp > 12 order by temp DESC, b.FirstName ASC;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, totalCredits FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NETID, SUM(Credits) totalCredits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS sumCredits WHERE totalCredits > 12 ORDER BY totalCredits DESC, FirstName ASC

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, c.SU  FROM Students as a,      (     SELECT NetId, SUM(credits) as SU     FROM Enrollments     GROUP BY NetId                     ) as c WHERE a.NetId = c.NetId and c.SU > 12 ORDER BY c.SU DESC, a.FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, a.total FROM     (     SELECT SUM(a.Credits) AS total, a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId     FROM         (         SELECT FirstName, LastName, s.NetId, e.Credits         FROM Enrollments AS e, Students AS s         WHERE e.NetId = s.NetId         ) AS a     GROUP BY a.NetId     ) AS b WHERE a.total > 12 ORDER BY a.total DESC, FirstName ASC

Select FirstName,LastName,Students.NetId,sum(Credits) from Students,Enrollments  where Students.NetId = Enrollments.NetId group by Students.NetId having sum(Credits) > 12 order by sum(Credits) DESC,FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName -- 12 < (SELECT SUM(Credits) --             FROM Enrollments b, Students a --             WHERE b.NetId = a.NetId)

SELECT      S.FirstName, S.LastName, S.NetId, SUM(E.Credits) FROM      Students AS S,      Enrollments AS E WHERE      S.NetId = E.NetID GROUP BY      E.NetId  /* use Group in order to you aggreation SUM */ HAVING      SUM(E.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY     SUM(E.Credits) DESC,     S.FirstName ASC
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, s FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) s FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId ) as temp WHERE s > 12 ORDER BY s DESC, FirstName

select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits)      FROM Students a JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId      GROUP BY b.NetId      HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12      ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName ASC;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) FROM Students a, Enrollments b WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;

SELECT FirstName, LastName, Students.NetId, Total FROM    Students,          (select NetId, SUM(Credits) as Total from Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) as TotalCredits WHERE Students.NetId = TotalCredits.NetId and Total > 12 ORDER BY Total DESC, FirstName

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, Credits FROM Students s LEFT JOIN (         SELECT minE.NetId AS NetId, sum(minE.Credits) AS Credits         FROM (             SELECT e.NetId AS NetId, e.Credits AS Credits             FROM Enrollments e             ) AS minE         GROUP BY minE.NetId     ) AS enr ON b.NetId = a.NetId WHERE Credits > 12 ORDER BY Credits DESC, FirstName
SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, SUM(Credits) total_credits FROM Students JOIN Enrollments USING(NetId) GROUP BY NetId HAVING total_credits > 12 ORDER BY total_credits DESC, FirstName ASC
Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, e.p from Students a, (select b, sum(Credits) as p from Enrollments group by NetId) e where a.NetId = e.NetId AND e.p > 12 order by e.p desc, a.FirstName asc;

Select a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, c.TCH From Students a, (Select b, Sum(Credits) as TCH from Enrollments group by NetId) as c Where a.NetId = c.NetId and c.TCH > 12 Order by c.TCH DESC, a.FirstName ASC

SELECT FirstName, LastName, NetId, TotalCredits FROM Students NATURAL JOIN (SELECT NetId, SUM(Credits) AS TotalCredits FROM Enrollments GROUP BY NetId) AS temp WHERE TotalCredits > 12 ORDER BY TotalCredits DESC, FirstName
SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetId, SUM(b.Credits) From Students a JOIN Enrollments b ON a.NetId = b.NetId GROUP BY b.NetId HAVING SUM(b.Credits) > 12 ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName;
