SELECT DISTINCT a.ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Products pr     JOIN Purchases b ON (a.ProductId = b.ProductId)     JOIN Customers c ON (b.CustomerId = c.CustomerId) WHERE a.BrandName = "Samsung" AND (c.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE "%4" OR c.CustomerId IN (     SELECT CustomerId     FROM Purchases purch JOIN Products prods ON (purch.ProductId = prods.ProductId)     WHERE prods.BrandName = "Apple" OR prods.BrandName = "Google" )) GROUP BY a.ProductName ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Customers c INNER JOIN Purchases p ON c.CustomerId = p.CustomerId INNER JOIN Products r on p.ProductId = r.ProductId WHERE r.ProductName = a.ProductName and (c.FirstName like 'J%' OR MOD(c.PhoneNumber,10) = 4 OR c.CustomerId IN (SELECT c3.CustomerId FROM Customers c3 INNER JOIN Purchases p3 ON c3.CustomerId = p3.CustomerId INNER JOIN Products r3 ON p3.ProductId = r3.ProductId WHERE r3.BrandName = 'Apple' OR r3.BrandName = 'Google'))) as cnt FROM Products p2 WHERE a.BrandName = 'Samsung' ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT ProductName, count(*) FROM (SELECT ProductName       FROM Customers C inner join Purchases P on C.CustomerId = P.CustomerId inner join Products Pr on P.ProductId = Pr.ProductId      WHERE BrandName = "Samsung"  AND (FirstName LIKE "J%" or PhoneNumber LIKE "%4"                                   or P.CustomerId in (SELECT A.CustomerId                                                     FROM Purchases A                                                     WHERE A.ProductId in (SELECT ProductId                                                                         FROM Products B                                                                         WHERE BrandName = "Apple"                                                                         or BrandName = "Google")                                                                         ))) AS G GROUP BY ProductName

select ProductName, (select count(*) from Customers c natural join Purchases natural join Products pp where pa.ProductName = a.ProductName and (c.FirstName like 'J%' or c.CustomerId in (select CustomerId from Purchases natural join Products where BrandName = "Google" or BrandName = "Apple") or c.PhoneNumber like '%4')) as cnt from Products a where a.BrandName = "Samsung" order by ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Customers NATURAL JOIN (             SELECT *             FROM Products             NATURAL JOIN Purchases             WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung'             )     AS joined WHERE CustomerId IN (                     SELECT CustomerId                     FROM Products                     NATURAL JOIN Purchases                     WHERE BrandName = 'Google'                         OR BrandName = 'Apple'                     )     OR PhoneNumber LIKE '%4'     OR FirstName LIKE 'J%' GROUP BY a.ProductId ORDER BY a.ProductName ASC;

SELECT b.ProductName, COUNT(c.CustomerId) FROM Customers a NATURAL JOIN Products b NATURAL JOIN Purchases p WHERE b.BrandName = "Samsung" AND (a.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR a.PhoneNumber mod 10 = 4 OR a.FirstName in (SELECT FirstName FROM Customers c1 NATURAL JOIN Purchases p1 NATURAL JOIN Products d1 WHERE BrandName = "Google" OR BrandName = "Apple")) GROUP by b.ProductName ORDER BY b.ProductName

SELECT DISTINCT ProductName, COUNT(CustomerId) FROM (  SELECT DISTINCT prod.ProductName, pur.CustomerId FROM Purchases pur, Products prod, Customers cus WHERE (pur.CustomerId = cus.CustomerId AND pur.ProductId = prod.ProductId AND prod.BrandName = "Samsung")     AND (cus.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR cus.PhoneNumber LIKE "%4" OR cus.CustomerId IN (SELECT CustomerId FROM Purchases WHERE ProductId IN (SELECT ProductId FROM Products WHERE BrandName = "Apple" OR BrandName = "Google")))  ) AS products_and_customers GROUP BY ProductName

select b.ProductName,count(*)  from  Purchases a natural join Products b natural join Customers c  where b.BrandName = 'Samsung' and           (c.FirstName like "J%" or c.PhoneNumber like "%4" or c.CustomerId in (      select C.CustomerId      from Customers C natural join Products P     where P.BrandName = 'Apple' or P.BrandName = 'Google'  ))   group by b.ProductName order by b.ProductName asc

SELECT PR1.ProductName, COUNT(C1.CustomerId) FROM Customers AS C1, Purchases AS PU1, Products AS PR1 WHERE C1.CustomerId = PU1.CustomerId     AND PU1.ProductId = PR1.ProductId     AND PR1.BrandName = 'Samsung'     AND (C1.FirstName LIKE 'J%'         OR C1.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4'         OR C1.CustomerId IN (SELECT C2.CustomerId             FROM Customers AS C2, Purchases AS PU2, Products AS PR2             WHERE C2.CustomerId = PU2.CustomerId                 AND PU2.ProductId = PR2.ProductId                 AND (PR2.BrandName = 'Apple'                     OR PR2.BrandName = 'Google'))) GROUP BY PR1.ProductId ORDER BY PR1.ProductName;

SELECT c.ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Customers a  LEFT JOIN Purchases b ON a.CustomerId = b.CustomerId LEFT JOIN Products c ON b.ProductId = c.ProductId WHERE c.BrandName = "Samsung" AND a.CustomerId IN  ( SELECT c.CustomerId FROM Customers c  LEFT JOIN Purchases p1 ON c.CustomerId = p1.CustomerId LEFT JOIN Products p2 ON p1.ProductId = p2.ProductId WHERE  c.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR MOD(c.PhoneNumber, 10) = 4 OR p2.BrandName = "Apple"  OR p2.BrandName = "Google" ) GROUP BY c.ProductName ORDER BY c.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(CustomerId) FROM Products NATURAL JOIN Purchases NATURAL JOIN Customers WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' AND (Firstname LIKE 'J%' OR PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR CustomerId in                                                  (SELECT CustomerId                                                 FROM Products NATURAL JOIN Purchases NATURAL JOIN Customers                                                 WHERE BrandName IN ('Apple', 'Google'))) GROUP BY ProductId ORDER BY ProductName

select table2.pro_name, count(table1.cid)  from (SELECT distinct c.customerid cid From Purchases pur, Customers c, Products pro where (left(c.Firstname, 1) = "J" or right(c.phonenumber ,1) = 4 or pro.brandname = "Google"      or pro.brandname = "Apple")  and c.customerid = pur.customerid and pur.ProductID = pro.productId )  as table1,  (SELECT  c.customerid cid, pro.productname pro_name From Customers c, Purchases pur, Products pro Where c.customerid = pur.customerid and pur.ProductID = pro.productId and pro.brandname = "Samsung") as table2 where table1.cid = table2.cid group by table2.pro_name

select Products.ProductName, count(Products.ProductId) from Products natural join Customers natural join Purchases   where Products.BrandName = 'Samsung' AND ( Customers.FirstName like 'J%' OR Customers.PhoneNumber like '%4' OR  Customers.CustomerId IN   (select Customers.CustomerId from ((Products inner join Purchases on Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId) inner join Customers on Purchases.CustomerId = Customers.CustomerId) where Products.BrandName = 'Apple' or Products.BrandName = 'Google')  ) group by Products.ProductName   order by Products.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, num FROM Products a NATURAL JOIN (     SELECT p1.ProductId, count(*) as num      FROM Purchases p1     WHERE p1.CustomerId IN (         SELECT Customers.CustomerId         FROM Customers         WHERE FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR PhoneNumber LIKE '%4'     ) OR p1.CustomerId IN (         SELECT p2.CustomerId         FROM Purchases p2 NATURAL JOIN Products pr2         WHERE pr2.BrandName = 'Apple' OR pr2.BrandName = 'Google'     ) GROUP BY p1.ProductId) as NumBought WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Products a NATURAL JOIN  (SELECT p1.ProductId  FROM Purchases p1 WHERE p1.CustomerId IN     (SELECT c.CustomerId FROM Customers c WHERE c.FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR c.CustomerId IN (SELECT p2.CustomerId FROM Purchases p2 WHERE p2.ProductId IN              (SELECT p3.ProductId FROM Products p3 WHERE p3.BrandName = 'Google' OR p3.BrandName = 'Apple')          )     ) ) AS X WHERE a.BrandName = 'Samsung' GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(ProductName) FROM ( SELECT CustomerId, ProductName FROM Purchases P, (SELECT ProductName, ProductId FROM Products WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung') as T WHERE P.ProductId = a.ProductId) as T GROUP BY ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM ((Products natural join Purchases) natural join Customers) WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' AND  (FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR PhoneNumber % 10 = 4 OR CustomerId IN (SELECT CustomerId FROM Products natural join Purchases where BrandName = 'Apple' OR BrandName = 'Google')) GROUP BY ProductName ORDER BY ProductName ASC;

SELECT c.ProductName,COUNT(*) FROM Customers a, Purchases b, Products c WHERE c.BrandName = 'Samsung'AND a.FirstName IN ( SELECT DISTINCT FirstName                   FROM Customers c, Purchases p1, Products p2                   WHERE c.FirstName LIKE 'J%'OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR ((p2.BrandName = 'Apple' OR p2.BrandName='Google') AND (c.CustomerId = p1.CustomerId AND p1.ProductId = p2.ProductId) )) AND a.CustomerId = b.CustomerId AND b.ProductId = c.ProductId GROUP BY c.ProductName ORDER BY c.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' AND CustomerId IN (SELECT DISTINCT CustomerId     FROM Customers     NATURAL JOIN Purchases     NATURAL JOIN Products     WHERE FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR BrandName IN ('Apple', 'Google')) GROUP BY ProductName ORDER BY ProductName

select Products.ProductName, Count(*) from Customers join Purchases on Customers.CustomerId = Purchases.CustomerId join Products on Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId where Products.BrandName = 'Samsung' and (Customers.FirstName like '%J' or Customers.PhoneNumber like '%4' or Customers.CustomerId in   (select Customers.CustomerId  from Customers join Purchases on Customers.CustomerId = Purchases.CustomerId join Products on Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId  where Products.BrandName = "Apple" or Products.BrandName = "Google"))  group by Products.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, b.CC FROM Products P      JOIN (SELECT P2.ProductId, COUNT(*) AS CC           FROM Purchases P2           RIGHT JOIN                  (SELECT DISTINCT C.CustomerId                 FROM Purchases P2                 JOIN Products a ON a.ProductId = P2.ProductId                 JOIN Customers C ON P2.CustomerId = C.CustomerId                 WHERE C.FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR                        C.PhoneNumber % 10 = 4 OR                       a.BrandName = 'Google' OR                       a.BrandName = 'Apple')           AS Conditions ON P2.CustomerId = Conditions.CustomerId           GROUP BY P2.ProductId      ) AS b ON a.ProductId = b.ProductId WHERE a.BrandName = 'Samsung'  ORDER BY a.ProductName

select a.ProductName, sum(a.productCount)     from (select pr.ProductName, count(p.ProductId) as productCount     from Purchases p inner join Products pr on p.ProductId = pr.ProductId inner join Customers c on p.CustomerId = c.CustomerId     group by pr.ProductName, pr.BrandName, c.FirstName, c.CustomerId, c.PhoneNumber having pr.BrandName = "Samsung" and (c.FirstName like "J*" or c.PhoneNumber like "%4" or c.CustomerId in (select p2.CustomerId from Purchases p2 inner join Products pr2 on p2.ProductId = pr2.ProductId where (pr2.BrandName = "Apple" or pr2.BrandName = "Google")))) as newTable group by ProductName;

SELECT ProductName, numCust FROM (SELECT pr.ProductName, COUNT(*) AS numCust        FROM Customers cust, Products pr, Purchases pu       WHERE pr.BrandName = "Samsung" AND cust.CustomerId = pu.CustomerId AND pr.ProductId = pu.ProductId AND cust.FirstName IN (SELECT DISTINCT cust1.FirstName FROM Customers cust1, Products pr1                                   , Purchases pu1                                             WHERE cust1.FirstName LIKE 'J%'                                             OR cust1.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4'                                             OR ((pu1.ProductId = pr1.ProductId AND cust1.CustomerId = pu1.CustomerId) AND (pr1.BrandName = "Apple" OR pr1.BrandName = "Google")))        GROUP BY pr.ProductName) AS a  ORDER BY ProductName ASC;

select ProductName, count(*) from Purchases natural join Products natural join Customers where BrandName = "Samsung" and (     FirstName like "J%"     or PhoneNumber like "%4"     or CustomerId in (         select CustomerId         from Purchases natural join Products         where BrandName = "Apple"         or BrandName = "Google"     ) ) group by ProductName order by ProductName;

SELECT ProductName, Count(CustomerId) FROM Products NATURAL JOIN Purchases WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' AND (CustomerId IN(SELECT CustomerId FROM Customers WHERE SUBSTRING(FirstName, 1, 1) = 'J') OR CustomerId IN(SELECT CustomerId FROM Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products WHERE BrandName = 'Apple' OR BrandName = 'Google') OR CustomerId IN(SELECT CustomerId FROM Customers WHERE Right(PhoneNumber, 1) = '4')) GROUP BY ProductName ORDER BY ProductName;

SELECT DISTINCT ProductName, Count(b.CustomerId) FROM Purchases a inner join Customers b on b.CustomerId=a.CustomerId inner join Products c on c.ProductId = a.ProductId WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' and b.CustomerId IN (SELECT DISTINCT b.CustomerId FROM Purchases a inner join Customers b on b.CustomerId=a.CustomerId inner join Products c on c.ProductId = a.ProductId WHERE FirstName LIKE 'J%' or PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' or BrandName = 'Apple' or BrandName = 'Google') GROUP BY (ProductName)

SELECT ProductName, counts FROM (     SELECT ProductName, ProductId, (SELECT COUNT(CustomerId)                                  FROM Purchases NATURAL JOIN Customers                                 WHERE p.ProductId=ProductId AND (FirstName LIKE "%J" OR PhoneNumber LIKE "%4" OR (CustomerId IN (SELECT CustomerId FROM Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products WHERE BrandName="Google" OR BrandName="Apple")))) as counts     FROM Products AS p     WHERE BrandName="Samsung" ) as samsung ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT b.ProductName, count(b.CustomerId) FROM(     (SELECT Purchases.CustomerId     FROM Purchases JOIN Products ON Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId     WHERE Products.BrandName = "Apple" OR Products.BrandName = "Google") UNION     (SELECT Customers.CustomerId     FROM Customers     WHERE Customers.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR Customers.PhoneNumber LIKE "%4")) AS a JOIN     (SELECT Purchases.CustomerId, Purchases.ProductId, Products.ProductName, Purchases.PurchaseId     FROM Purchases JOIN Products ON Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId     WHERE Products.BrandName = "Samsung") AS BT     ON b.CustomerId = a.CustomerId GROUP BY b.ProductName;

SELECT Products.ProductName, COUNT(Purchases.CustomerId) FROM Products INNER JOIN Purchases ON Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId INNER JOIN Customers ON Customers.CustomerId = Purchases.CustomerId WHERE Products.BrandName = 'Samsung'  AND Customers.CustomerId IN (SELECT C.CustomerId FROM Customers C, Purchases P WHERE C.CustomerId = P.CustomerId AND ((C.FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR RIGHT(C.PhoneNumber, 1) = 4) OR (P.CustomerId IN (SELECT P2.CustomerId FROM Purchases P2, Products Pr WHERE (Pr.BrandName = 'Apple' or Pr.BrandName = 'Google') AND P2.ProductId = Pr.ProductId)))) GROUP BY Products.ProductId ORDER BY Products.ProductName ASC;

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(CustomerId) FROM ( 	SELECT Products.BrandName, Products.ProductName, res.CustomerId 	FROM Products 	JOIN 	( 		SELECT * 		FROM Purchases 		WHERE  		(CustomerId IN( 			SELECT CustomerId 			FROM Purchases 			WHERE ProductId IN 			(SELECT ProductId 			FROM Products 			WHERE BrandName = 'Apple' OR BrandName = 'Google') 		)) OR 		(CustomerId IN 			(SELECT CustomerId 			 FROM (SELECT Customers.CustomerId, Customers.FirstName, Customers.PhoneNumber, Purchases.PurchaseId 						FROM Customers  						JOIN Purchases 						ON Customers.CustomerId = Purchases.CustomerId) AS l 			 WHERE l.FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR l.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4') 		) 	) AS res 	ON res.ProductId = Products.ProductId ) AS list1 WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' GROUP By ProductName ORDER BY ProductName ASC

select a.ProductName,      (select count(c.CustomerId)      from Purchases pr left join Customers c on c.CustomerId = pr.CustomerId     where (pr.ProductId = a.ProductId and (c.CustomerId in (       select pr2.CustomerId from Purchases pr2         left join Products p2 on pr2.ProductId = p2.ProductId      where p2.BrandName = 'Apple' or p2.BrandName = 'Google')       or c.FirstName like 'J%' or c.PhoneNumber % 10 = 4)))       as variable from Products a where a.BrandName = 'Samsung' having variable > 0 order by a.ProductName;

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(ProductName) FROM Customers NATURAL JOIN Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products WHERE BrandName = 'Samsung' AND CustomerId IN (SELECT CustomerId FROM Customers NATURAL JOIN Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products WHERE FirstName = 'J%' OR PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR BrandName = 'APPLE' OR BrandName = 'Google') GROUP BY ProductName ORDER BY ProductName ASC

SELECT Products.ProductName, Count(Purchases.CustomerId) FROM Purchases, Products,     (SELECT CustomerId     FROM Customers     WHERE FirstName LIKE "J%"     UNION     SELECT CustomerId     FROM Customers     WHERE PhoneNumber LIKE "%4"     UNION     SELECT Purchases.CustomerId     FROM Purchases, Products     WHERE Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId and (Products.BrandName = "Apple" or Products.BrandName = "Google"))     as STRANGE WHERE  Purchases.ProductId = Products.ProductId and Products.BrandName = "Samsung"      and Purchases.CustomerId IN (STRANGE.CustomerId) GROUP BY Products.ProductName ORDER BY Products.ProductName

SELECT pr.ProductName, COUNT(pr.ProductName) FROM(SELECT c.CustomerId     FROM Customers c     WHERE c.FirstName LIKE 'J%'            OR CAST(c.PhoneNumber as Char) LIKE '%4'            OR (c.CustomerId in (SELECT c.CustomerId                                FROM  Products pr, Purchases pu, Customers c                                WHERE c.CustomerId = pu.CustomerId                                       and pu.ProductId = pr.ProductId                                       and (pr.BrandName = 'Apple' or pr.BrandName = 'Google')                                )               )     )AS a, Purchases pu, Products pr WHERE a.CustomerId = pu.CustomerId and pu.ProductId = pr.ProductId and pr.BrandName = 'Samsung' GROUP BY pr.ProductName

Select ProductName,count(*) from Products Natural Join Purchases where BrandName="Samsung" and CustomerId  IN  ( Select DISTINCT C.CustomerId from Customers C,Purchases P, Products P1 where C.CustomerId=P.CustomerId and P.ProductId=P1.ProductId and (C.Firstname LIKE "J%" or C.PhoneNumber LIKE "%4" or C.Customerid IN  ( Select DISTINCT X.CustomerId from Purchases X,Products Y where X.ProductId=Y.ProductId and (Y.Brandname="Apple" or Y.BrandName="Google") ) ) ) group by ProductName order by ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COUNT(*) FROM Products pr     JOIN Purchases d        ON a.ProductID = d.ProductID     JOIN Brands b       ON a.BrandName = d.Brandname     JOIN Customers c       ON d.CustomerId = d.CustomerId WHERE      d.Brandname = "Samsung"     AND      (SUBSTRING(d.FirstName, 1, 1) = "J"         OR d.PhoneNumber % 10 = 4         OR d.CustomerId IN (SELECT d.CustomerId                               FROM Products pr                                  JOIN Purchases d                                     ON a.ProductID = d.ProductID                                  JOIN Brands b                                    ON a.BrandName = d.Brandname                                  JOIN Customers c                                    ON d.CustomerId = d.CustomerId                             WHERE d.BrandName = "Google"                                OR d.BrandName = "Apple")         ) GROUP BY ProductName ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT c.ProductName,COUNT(*) FROM Customers a, Purchases b, Products c WHERE c.BrandName = 'Samsung'AND a.FirstName IN ( SELECT DISTINCT FirstName                   FROM Customers c, Purchases p1, Products p2                   WHERE c.FirstName LIKE 'J%'OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR ((p2.BrandName = 'Apple' OR p2.BrandName='Google') AND (c.CustomerId = p1.CustomerId AND p1.ProductId = p2.ProductId) )) AND a.CustomerId = b.CustomerId AND b.ProductId = c.ProductId GROUP BY c.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, b.Total FROM Products as Pr INNER JOIN (     SELECT ProductId, COUNT(*) as Total      FROM Purchases     INNER JOIN (         SELECT * FROM Customers     ) AS c ON c.CustomerId=Purchases.CustomerId     WHERE c.FirstName LIKE 'J%' OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR EXISTS (         SELECT * FROM Purchases         INNER JOIN Products ON Purchases.ProductId=Products.ProductId         WHERE Purchases.CustomerId=c.CustomerId AND (Products.BrandName = 'Apple' OR Products.BrandName = 'Google')     )     GROUP BY ProductId ) AS b ON a.ProductId=b.ProductId WHERE BrandName="Samsung" AND b.Total <> 0 ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, countCustomer FROM Products products JOIN (     SELECT pt.ProductId, count(pt.CustomerId) AS countCustomer     FROM Purchases pt     WHERE pt.CustomerId = ANY (         SELECT c.CustomerId         FROM Customers c         WHERE c.FirstName LIKE "%J"         OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE "%4"         OR c.CustomerId = ANY(             SELECT pur.CustomerId             FROM Purchases pur             JOIN Products pro             ON pro.ProductId = pur.ProductId             WHERE BrandName = "Google"             OR BrandName = "Apple"         )     )     GROUP BY pt.ProductId ) AS ppur ON a.ProductId = b.ProductId WHERE a.BrandName = "Samsung" ORDER BY a.ProductName

select ProductName, count(Purchases.CustomerId) from Products a, Purchases where Purchases.CustomerId in (select c.CustomerId from Customers c where c.FirstName like 'J%' or cast(PhoneNumber as char) like '%4' or c.CustomerId in (select CustomerId from Purchases where ProductId in (select ProductId from Products where BrandName = 'Apple' or BrandName = 'Google'))) and a.ProductId = Purchases.ProductId and BrandName = 'Samsung' group by ProductName order by ProductName asc;

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.ProductName) FROM Products a, Purchases NATURAL JOIN Customers WHERE a.BrandName = "Samsung" AND a.ProductId = Purchases.ProductId AND (Customers.FirstName LIKE "J%" OR Customers.PhoneNumber % 4 = 0 OR Customers.CustomerId IN(         SELECT CustomerId         FROM Purchases NATURAL JOIN Products         WHERE BrandName = "Apple" OR BrandName = "Google"     )) GROUP BY a.ProductName ORDER BY a.ProductName;

SELECT a.ProductName, ( SELECT count(*) FROM Customers WHERE (PhoneNumber Like '%4' OR FirstName like 'J%' OR CustomerId IN ( SELECT P2.CustomerId  FROM (SELECT *     FROM Purchases natural join Products) P2     WHERE P2.BrandName = 'Apple' OR P2.BrandName = 'Google'     )) and CustomerId in (     SELECT CustomerId FROM Purchases P3 WHERE P3.ProductId = a.ProductId)     ) + 1 as num FROM Products P1 WHERE a.BrandName = 'Samsung' ORDER by a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.PurchaseId) FROM Products a JOIN Purchases b ON a.ProductId = b.ProductId WHERE a.BrandName = "Samsung"  AND b.CustomerId IN (SELECT c.CustomerId                         FROM Customers c                         WHERE (SUBSTRING(c.FirstName, 1, 1) = "J" ) OR c.PhoneNumber LIKE '%4' OR c.CustomerId IN                          (SELECT pur.CustomerId                         FROM Purchases pur                          JOIN Products p2 ON (p2.ProductId = pur.ProductId)                         WHERE (p2.BrandName = "Google" OR p2.BrandName = "Apple"))) GROUP BY a.ProductName ORDER BY a.ProductName ASC

select a.ProductName, count(b.ProductId) from     Products a left join Products b on a.BrandName = b.BrandName and a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased group by a.ProductId, a.ProductName order by a.ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName,SUM(     if(a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased, 1, 0)) FROM Products a LEFT JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName WHERE a.BrandName = b.BrandName GROUP BY a.ProductName

select a.ProductName, count(a.ProductName) - 1 from Products a join Products b on a.BrandName = b.BrandName where a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased or a.ProductName = b.ProductName group by a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT count(*)                    FROM Products                    WHERE (a.BrandName = BrandName) AND (a.YearReleased > YearReleased)) From Products P ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COALESCE(c, 0) FROM Products LEFT JOIN (         SELECT p1.ProductName AS Prod1, COUNT(p1.ProductId) AS c         FROM Products p1, Products p2         WHERE p2.YearReleased < p1.YearReleased         AND p1.BrandName = p2.BrandName         GROUP BY Prod1     ) AS a ON Products.ProductName = a.Prod1 ORDER BY ProductName ASC
Select a.ProductName, (Select count(*) From Products Where a.BrandName = BrandName And a.YearReleased > YearReleased) From Products p Order by a.ProductName
select a.ProductName,      (select count(*)      from Products as b      where a.BrandName = b.BrandName and a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) from Products as a order by a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.ProductName) - 1 FROM Products a, (SELECT * FROM Products) AS TEMP WHERE a.BrandName = TEMa.BrandName AND (a.YearReleased > TEMa.YearReleased OR a.ProductName = TEMa.ProductName) GROUP BY a.ProductName

select a.ProductName, count(a.ProductName) - 1 from Products as a  join Products as b on (a.BrandName = Pa.BrandName and a.YearReleased > Pa.YearReleased) or (a.BrandName = Pa.BrandName and a.ProductName = Pa.ProductName) group by a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName AS curr_prod, (SELECT COUNT(a.ProductName) FROM Products a, Products p2 WHERE a.ProductName = curr_prod AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = b.BrandName) FROM Products a, Products b WHERE a.BrandName = b.BrandName GROUP BY a.ProductName;

select Products.ProductName, coalesce(a.c, 0) from Products left join (select a.ProductName as p, count(*) as c from Products a left outer join Products b on a.BrandName = b.BrandName where a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased group by a.ProductName) a on a.p = Products.ProductName order by Products.ProductName asc
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products AS awk1 left join Products AS b on a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductName

select ProductName, (select count(*)                     from Products p2                     where p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and p2.BrandName = a.BrandName) from Products p1 order by a.ProductName
select a.ProductName, count(b.YearReleased) from Products a left join Products as b  on a.BrandName = b.BrandName and a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased group by a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName,     (SELECT COUNT(ProductName) FROM Products AS P2         WHERE Products.YearReleased > P2.YearReleased AND Products.BrandName = P2.BrandName)     FROM Products     ORDER BY ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(prod2.ProductId) FROM Products as prod2 WHERE a.BrandName = prod2.BrandName AND prod2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) FROM Products as prod ORDER BY a.ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductId) FROM Products A LEFT JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductId ORDER BY a.ProductName;
select a.ProductName, (select count(1) from Products as a1 where a.BrandName = a1.BrandName and a1.YearReleased < a.YearReleased ) as num from Products a ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, 0 as count_before FROM Products  WHERE ProductName NOT IN (SELECT a.ProductName FROM Products a, Products p2 WHERE a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BRANDNAME = b.BRANDNAME GROUP BY a.ProductName) UNION ALL SELECT a.ProductName as ProductName, count(b.ProductName) as count_before FROM Products a, Products p2  WHERE a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BRANDNAME = b.BRANDNAME  GROUP BY a.ProductName ORDER BY ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName, (     SELECT COUNT(*)     FROM Products p1     WHERE p1.YearReleased < a.YearReleased     AND a.BrandName = p1.BrandName ) FROM Products p ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductId) FROM Products P LEFT OUTER JOIN (SELECT P1.ProductId FROM Products P1, Products P2 WHERE P1.YearReleased > P2.YearReleased AND P1.BrandName = P2.BrandName) as RealCounts ON a.ProductId = b.ProductId GROUP BY a.ProductId ORDER BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, SUM(a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT new.ProductName, COUNT(old.ProductId)-1 FROM Products new, Products old WHERE (new.YearReleased > old.YearReleased and new.BrandName = old.BrandName) or (new.YearReleased = old.YearReleased and new.ProductName = old.productName) GROUP BY new.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName,  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Products as P2  WHERE a.BrandName = P2.BrandName  AND P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) FROM Products as P1 ORDER BY a.ProductName

Select ProductName, (Select Count(*)                      From Products temp                      Where BrandName = Current.BrandName AND                      Current.YearReleased > YearReleased ) From Products Current Order By ProductName
select a.ProductName, count(b.ProductId) from Products as a left join Products as b on a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased and a.BrandName = b.BrandName group by a.ProductName;

SELECT new.ProductName, COUNT(prior.ProductId) FROM Products new LEFT OUTER JOIN Products prior     ON new.BrandName = prior.BrandName AND new.YearReleased > prior.YearReleased GROUP BY new.ProductId ORDER BY new.ProductName;

select a.ProductName, ifnull(b.cts, 0) from Products p7 LEFT JOIN (select p3.ProductName, p4.cts from Products p3, (select p5.ProductName,count(p5.bProductId) as cts from (select p1.ProductName, p2.ProductId as bProductId from Products p1, Products p2 where p1.BrandName = p2.BrandName and p1.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased) p5 group by p5.ProductName) p4 where p3.ProductName = p4.ProductName) p6 on a.ProductName = b.ProductName order by a.ProductName
SELECT ProductName,  (SELECT COUNT(*)     FROM Products AS p2     WHERE p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and p2.BrandName = a.BrandName      ) FROM Products AS p ORDER BY ProductName;
select p1.ProductName, count(p2.ProductId) from (Products p1 left join Products p2 on p1.BrandName=p2.BrandName and p1.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased) group by p1.ProductId order by p1.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (     SELECT COUNT(b.ProductId)     FROM Products b     WHERE a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = b.BrandName) FROM Products a ORDER BY ProductName ASC
Select a.ProductName, Count(b.YearReleased) From Products a Left Outer Join Products B     on a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased and a.BrandName = b.BrandName Group By a.ProductName

select b.ProductName, coalesce ( a.ct,0) from (select p1.ProductName, count(p2.ProductName) as ct from Products p1, Products p2 where p2.BrandName = p1.Brandname and p2.YearReleased < p1.YearReleased group by p1.ProductName) as a right outer join Products b on a.ProductName = b.ProductName order by b.ProductName asc

select a.ProductName,(select count(P2.ProductId)                      from Products P2                      where P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and a.BrandName = P2.BrandName) from Products P1 order by a.ProductName
select a.ProductName, (select count(*) from Products C where C.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and C.BrandName = a.BrandName) as _prodCount from Products P order by a.ProductName ASC;
SELECT new.ProductName, COUNT(old.ProductId) FROM Products old RIGHT OUTER JOIN Products new ON old.BrandName=new.BrandName AND new.YearReleased > old.YearReleased  GROUP BY new.ProductName;

SELECT Products.ProductName, COALESCE(op, 0) FROM Products LEFT JOIN (     SELECT now.ProductName as help1, COUNT(old.ProductId) as op     FROM Products now, Products old     WHERE now.BrandName = old.BrandName AND now.YearReleased > old.YearReleased GROUP BY now.ProductName     ) AS a ON Products.ProductName = a.help1 ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT ProductName, counts  FROM (SELECT ProductName, BrandName,      (SELECT COUNT(ProductName)      FROM Products      WHERE T1.YearReleased > YearReleased AND T1.BrandName = BrandName) AS counts FROM Products AS T1) AS T2 ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COALESCE((SELECT COUNT(*) 						FROM Products P2 						WHERE a.BrandName = P2.BrandName AND a.ProductName <> P2.ProductName AND P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased                         GROUP BY P2.BrandName), 0) FROM Products P1 ORDER BY a.ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductId) FROM Products pr1 LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b  ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(p2.YearReleased)                        FROM Products p2                        WHERE p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND p2.BrandName = a.BrandName) FROM Products p ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, (     SELECT COUNT(P2.ProductId)     FROM (Products P2 INNER JOIN Brands B2 ON B2.BrandName = P2.BrandName)     WHERE P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = P2.BrandName ) FROM Products P1 ORDER BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) - 1 FROM Products a JOIN Products Pr ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName WHERE (a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) OR (a.ProductName = b.ProductName) GROUP BY a.ProductName;

SELECT     a.ProductName,     ifnull(b.cnt, 0) FROM      Products a      LEFT OUTER JOIN      (SELECT         a.ProductId,         count(*) as cnt     FROM         Products P,         Products PP     WHERE          a.YearReleased > Pa.YearReleased         AND         a.BrandName = Pa.BrandName         AND         a.ProductId <> Pa.ProductId     GROUP by         a.ProductId     ) as t         on a.ProductId = b.ProductId ORDER by     a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*)                     FROM Products a                     WHERE a.YearReleased > a.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = a.BrandName)                      FROM Products p ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, SUM(CASE WHEN a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased then 1 else 0 end) as Products_released_before FROM Products AS p LEFT JOIN Products AS b ON a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = b.BrandName group by a.ProductName;

Select  a.ProductName,  Count(p2.ProductId) - 1 From Products a,  Products p2 -- on   -- a.ProductId <> p2.ProductId Where  (a.BrandName = p2.BrandName and a.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased) or a.ProductName = p2.ProductName Group by a.ProductId order by a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Products b WHERE a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) FROM Products a #LEFT JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName #GROUP BY a.ProductName ORDER BY a.ProductName  /**  put a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased somewhere else? it's filtering out results with 0  because those results don't have a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased */

SELECT a.ProductName, Count(b.ProductId) as p2Previous_Products FROM Products as a      LEFT OUTER JOIN Products as b        ON (a.BrandName = b.BrandName       AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) GROUP BY a.ProductName, a.ProductId
SELECT a.ProductName, Count(b.ProductName) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON (a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) AND (a.BrandName = b.BrandName) Group By a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COALESCE(c, 0) FROM Products LEFT JOIN (         SELECT p1.ProductName AS Prod1, COUNT(p1.ProductId) AS c         FROM Products p1, Products p2         WHERE p2.YearReleased < p1.YearReleased         AND p1.BrandName = p2.BrandName         GROUP BY Prod1     ) AS a ON Products.ProductName = a.Prod1 ORDER BY ProductName ASC
SELECT a.ProductName, SUM(CASE WHEN (a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = b.BrandName)  THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM Products a, Products b GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.ProductName) - 1 FROM Products a JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName WHERE b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased OR a.ProductName = b.ProductName GROUP BY a.ProductName;

Select a.ProductName, Count(b.YearReleased) From Products a left outer join Products b on a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased and a.BrandName = b.BrandName Group by a.ProductName  -- SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, a.NetID, SUM(b.Credits) -- FROM Students A, Enrollments B -- WHERE a.NetId = b.NetId -- Group BY b.NetId  -- Having SUM(b.Credits)>12 -- ORDER BY SUM(b.Credits) DESC, a.FirstName
select ProductName,  (select count(*)   from Products Pro2   where Pro2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and Pro2.BrandName = a.BrandName) from Products Pro order by ProductName

SELECT ProductName, COALESCE(ct, 0) FROM Products P LEFT JOIN (     SELECT P1.ProductName AS prodName, COUNT(P1.ProductId) AS ct     FROM Products P1, Products P2     WHERE P2.YearReleased < P1.YearReleased AND P1.BrandName = P2.BrandName     GROUP BY prodName ) AS b ON a.ProductName = b.prodName ORDER BY ProductName ASC

select a.ProductName, (select count(p2.YearReleased) from Products p2 where a.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased and a.BrandName = p2.BrandName)  from Products a  order by a.productName -- having a.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased; -- where a.YearReleased < b.YearEstablished -- group by a.ProductName ;

SELECT a.ProductName,    (SELECT count(t2.ProductId)    FROM Products t2      WHERE a.YearReleased > t2.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = t2.BrandName    ) AS number_product_release_early  FROM Products a  order by a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ProductId)                 FROM Products B                 WHERE B.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and B.BrandName = a.BrandName )  From Products A ORDER BY LOWER(ProductName);
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(D.ProductName) FROM Products D WHERE D.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = D.BrandName) FROM Products C ORDER BY a.ProductName;
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT Count(*) From Products P2 Where P2.BrandName=a.BrandName and P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) FROM Products P1 ORDER BY ProductName
select ProductName, (     select count(*) from Products where YearReleased < a.YearReleased and BrandName=a.BrandName ) from Products as Current order by ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName, SUM(a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) FROM Products Prod JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName GROUP BY a.ProductName
select    a.ProductName,   (select count(*) from Products where BrandName = a.BrandName AND YearReleased < a.YearReleased) count from Products t order by ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, count(a.BrandName)-1 FROM Products a, Products b WHERE a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND (a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased  OR      (a.ProductId = b.ProductId AND a.YearReleased = b.YearReleased)) GROUP BY a.ProductName
select ProductName,(Select count(*) from Products b where a.BrandName=b.BrandName and b.YearReleased<a.YearReleased) from Products a Order by ProductName ASC;
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*)     FROM Products p2     WHERE a.BrandName = p2.BrandName AND p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased ) FROM Products p1 ORDER BY a.ProductName ASC

SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*)                         FROM Products p                         WHERE a.BrandName = p.BrandName and a.YearReleased > p.YearReleased) FROM Products p2 ORDER BY a.ProductName
select ProductName, (select count(*) from Products where YearReleased < a.YearReleased and BrandName = a.BrandName) as cnt from Products a order by ProductName

SELECT ProductName, (     SELECT COUNT(ProductName)     FROM Products AS ProductsBefore     WHERE Products.YearReleased > ProductsBefore.YearReleased          AND Products.BrandName = ProductsBefore.BrandName ) FROM Products ORDER BY ProductName ASC;

SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*)-1 FROM Products p2 WHERE ((p2.YearReleased <a.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = p2.BrandName) OR (p2.ProductId = a.ProductId AND p2.YearReleased=a.YearReleased)) GROUP by p2.BrandName) FROM Products d GROUP By a.BrandName, a.ProductName, a.YearReleased, a.ProductId ORDER By a.ProductName

select ProductName,count(ProductId) from (select p.ProductName, p.ProductId as ProductMainId, pp.ProductId from Products p left outer join Products pp on p.BrandName = pp.BrandName and p.YearReleased > pp.YearReleased) as ppp group by ProductMainId order by ProductName

SELECT p1Name, COUNT(p2Name) FROM (SELECT P1.ProductName AS p1Name, P2.ProductName AS p2Name     FROM Products P1     LEFT JOIN Products P2 ON P1.YearReleased > P2.YearReleased         AND P1.BrandName = P2.BrandName) AS productInfo GROUP BY p1Name;
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductId) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductId ORDER BY a.ProductName
select a.ProductName,  (select count(*) from Products where Yearreleased < a.yearreleased and a.brandname = brandname) from Products p order by a.ProductName;

SELECT prd1, COUNT(null_check) FROM (SELECT p1.productName as prd1, p2.productName as null_check FROM Products p1 LEFT OUTER JOIN Products p2 on      p1.BrandName = p2.BrandName and p1.YearReleased > p2.YearReleased) as t GROUP BY prd1
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.ProductId)-1 FROM Products a, Products b WHERE (a.BrandName=b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) OR a.ProductId=b.ProductId GROUP BY a.ProductName

select a.ProductName, count(b.productId) from Products as p1 left outer join Products as p2 on a.BrandName = b.BrandName  and a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased group by a.ProductID order by a.ProductName
select a.ProductName, (select count(*) from Products pr2 where pr2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and pr2.BrandName = a.BrandName) from Products pr order by a.ProductName;

SELECT a.ProductName, IFNULL(Num, 0) FROM Products as a LEFT JOIN (SELECT p2.ProductName as name, count(*) AS Num FROM Products as p1, Products as p2 WHERE p1.BrandName = p2.BrandName AND p1.YearReleased < p2.YearReleased GROUP BY p2.ProductName) AS NumProducts ON a.ProductName = b.name ORDER BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products a LEFT JOIN Products b  ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT b.ProductName, coalesce(a.pre, 0) FROM (SELECT P1.ProductName, COUNT(P2.ProductName) AS pre FROM Products P1, Products P2 WHERE P1.BrandName = P2.BrandName and P1.YearReleased > P2.YearReleased GROUP BY P1.ProductName) AS a RIGHT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.ProductName = b.ProductName ORDER BY b.ProductName
SELECT ProductName, (select count(*) from Products p where p.BrandName = Products.BrandName AND p.YearReleased < Products.YearReleased) FROM Products order by ProductName ASC;
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductID) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON     a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductID ORDER BY a.ProductName;
SELECT a.ProductName,COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products P1 LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.ProductId <> b.ProductId AND b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(*) - 1 FROM Products P1      JOIN (SELECT ProductName, YearReleased, BrandName            FROM Products)             AS b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName WHERE a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased OR a.ProductName = b.ProductName GROUP BY a.ProductName
select a.ProductName, count(b.ProductName)  from Products a left join Products b on b.BrandName = a.BrandName and b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased group by a.ProductName

SELECT ProductName, NumProds FROM (SELECT prod1.ProductName, COUNT(prod2.ProductId) AS NumProds       FROM Products prod1 LEFT OUTER JOIN Products prod2 ON (prod1.BrandName = prod2.BrandName AND       prod1.YearReleased > prod2.YearReleased)        GROUP BY prod1.ProductName) AS T

SELECT  a.ProductName, count(b.ProductName)-- a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN  Products b      ON (a.BrandName=b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased) GROUP BY a.ProductName
select a.ProductName, sum(if(b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased, 1, 0)) from Products a inner join Products p2 on a.BrandName = b.BrandName group by a.ProductName order by a.ProductName
SELECT A.ProductName, COUNT(CASE WHEN (A.BrandName = B.BrandName AND A.YearReleased > B.YearReleased) THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS PrevProducts FROM Products AS A, Products AS B GROUP BY A.ProductName;
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(ProductId) FROM Products p2 WHERE p2.BrandName=a.BrandName AND p2.YearReleased<a.YearReleased) FROM Products p1 ORDER BY ProductName ASC

SELECT ProductName, counts FROM  (     SELECT ProductName, BrandName,          (SELECT COUNT(ProductName) FROM Products WHERE Final.YearReleased > YearReleased AND Final.BrandName = BrandName) as counts     FROM Products     AS Final ) AS prodCounts ORDER BY ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(a.result) FROM     (SELECT pp.ProductName, A.ProductName AS result     FROM Products pp LEFT OUTER JOIN Products A ON pp.YearReleased > A.YearReleased         AND pp.BrandName = A.BrandName     AND pp.ProductId <> A.ProductId) AS bt GROUP BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(case when b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and b.BrandName = a.BrandName then 1 end) FROM Products a  CROSS JOIN Products B GROUP BY a.ProductName;

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) AS number FROM Products AS a LEFT JOIN Products AS b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased GROUP BY a.ProductId ORDER BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductId) FROM Products p1   LEFT JOIN Products b ON (b.BrandName = a.BrandName AND b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) GROUP BY a.ProductName
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT count(*) FROM Products p2 WHERE p2.BrandName = a.BrandName AND p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) FROM Products p1 ORDER BY ProductName ASC

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM    (SELECT distinct p.ProductName          FROM Products p          )AS c  LEFT JOIN   (SELECT a.ProductName, a.YearReleased             FROM(SELECT p.BrandName, p.YearReleased, p.ProductName                  FROM Products p, Brands b                  WHERE p.BrandName = b.BrandName ) AS a, Products pr             WHERE a.BrandName = pr.BrandName and a.YearReleased > pr.YearReleased             ) AS b ON a.ProductName = b.ProductName GROUP BY a.ProductName

Select a.ProductName, ( Select count(ProductId) from Brands NATURAL JOIN Products where YearReleased < a.YearReleased and BrandName=b.BrandName ) from Products a, Brands b where a.BrandName=b.BrandName order by a.ProductName ASC

SELECT      ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(P2.ProductId)                      FROM Products P2                     WHERE P2.BrandName = a.BrandName                       AND P2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) AS number FROM         Products P1 ORDER BY     ProductName ASC
SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.ProductName) FROM Products a LEFT OUTER JOIN Products b ON a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased  GROUP BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT Count(*) FROM Products pr2 WHERE a.BrandName = pr2.BrandName AND pr2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) FROM Products a ORDER BY a.ProductName ASC;

SELECT Products.ProductName, COALESCE(amount, 0) FROM Products LEFT JOIN (         SELECT curr.ProductName AS name, COUNT(curr.ProductId) AS amount         FROM Products curr, Products pre         WHERE curr.BrandName = pre.BrandName AND curr.YearReleased > pre.YearReleased         GROUP BY name     ) AS a ON Products.ProductName = a.name ORDER BY ProductName;
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Products i WHERE i.YearReleased < a.YearReleased and i.BrandName = a.BrandName) FROM Products AS o ORDER BY ProductName

Select ProductName, count(earlier) FROM Products oriP LEFT JOIN (     SELECT pb.ProductID AS earlier, pb.BrandName AS bn, pb.YearReleased AS yr     FROM Products pp ) AS p ON b.bn = a.BrandName AND b.yr < a.YearReleased GROUP BY ProductName, ProductId, BrandName, YearReleased
Select a.ProductName, count(b.ProductName) from Products a left outer join Products b on a.BrandName = b.BrandName and b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased group by a.ProductName
select b.ProductName, Count(*)-1 from Products a join Products b  where a.BrandName = b.BrandName and (b.YearReleased > a.YearReleased or b.ProductName = a.ProductName) group by b.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, SUM(CASE WHEN a.YearReleased > b.YearReleased && a.BrandName = b.BrandName THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM Products a, Products b GROUP BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(p1.BrandName) FROM Products p1 WHERE (p1.BrandName = a.BrandName) AND (p1.YearReleased < a.YearReleased)) AS numProds FROM Products p ORDER BY a.ProductName;
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Products Pro2 WHERE Pro2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND Pro2.BrandName = a.BrandName) FROM Products Pro ORDER by ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (Select count(ProductId) from Products  where a.BrandName = BrandName and a.YearReleased > YearReleased) FROM Products item ORDER BY a.ProductName
SELECT a.ProductName, (Select Count(*) From Products p2 Where p2.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND a.BrandName = p2.BrandName) From Products a  Order By a.ProductName

SELECT a.ProductName, COUNT(b.YearReleased) - 1 FROM Products as a, Products as b WHERE (a.BrandName = b.BrandName AND b.YearReleased < a.YearReleased) OR       (a.ProductName = b.ProductName) GROUP BY a.ProductName;
SELECT ProductName, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Products p WHERE  p.YearReleased < a.YearReleased AND p.BrandName = a.BrandName) FROM Products x ORDER BY ProductName
